title: 2 minute cookies
directions: Mix together in large saucepan the first 5 ingredients and bring to a boil. Boil exactly 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add last 4 ingredients. Quickly stir and drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Blend lemon juice, egg yolks and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Blend in sugar.
Mix well and put on pie.
Brown in 350° oven.
Refrigerate.

title: barbeque beef
directions: Brown
ground
beef.
Drain.
Mix
roast beef and ground beef together.
Put in Manwich and barbecue sauce.
Heat for a few minutes with continued stirring.

title: banana pops
directions: In a blender, combine the yogurt, orange juice and banana; cover and process until smooth.
Pour into popsicle trays or pour into small plastic disposable cups and insert popsicle sticks. Freeze until firm, about 5 hours or overnight.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets and cook in salted water until tender.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Thaw soup and pour over cauliflower.
Sprinkle with cheese and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: working cow girls casserole
directions: Cook and cream potatoes. Put potatoes in casserole and using a spoon, hollow out hole in center about the size of a saucer. Brown hamburger with onion; drain. Fill hole in potatoes with hamburger. Cover the top with grated cheese. Place in oven until cheese melts.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies as directed on package.
Allow to cool completely.
Crumble into bottom of clear glass bowl.
In a large Ziploc bag, crush candy bars.
Sprinkle over brownies; do not mix. Prepare mousse as directed on package except increase milk by 1/2 of amount called for on package.
Pour over brownie-candy bar mixture.
Do not mix but make slits in mixture so that mousse can seep to bottom of bowl.
Spread nondairy whipped topping over mousse.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill 24 hours before serving.
Yields 8 to 12 servings.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine cake mix, margarine, eggs, and water; mix well. Add chocolate pieces; dough will be stiff. Drop by rounded tablespoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: baked corn
directions: Brown pepper and onion in 2 tablespoons butter for 5 minutes. Add flour, salt, paprika and mustard; stir until blended.
Add milk; stir until thick.
Brown bread crumbs in 1 tablespoon butter; add crumbs, corn and egg to onion and pepper mixture. Bake in buttered dish for 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix altogether.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle on top 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and sugar until crumbly; put in bottom of crust. Save some for pie topping.

title: ham casserole
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, ham and onion powder in an ungreased rectangular baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Mix Bisquick and milk; pour evenly over soup mixture. Bake 27 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: timmy's pie crust
directions: Sprinkle the ice water over mixture, then toss with a fork. Roll out 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured surface.
For cream pies, bake crust 10 minutes at 450°.
Be sure to prick dough all over to prevent air bubbles.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix oats, flour and sugar.
Add margarine and stir until mixture is crumbly.
Place half the mixture in well greased 8 x 8-inch pan and cover with cranberry sauce.
Top with the
balance of the oat mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve warm, topped with whipped cream.

title: curtis' pinto beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook overnight and it will be ready at lunch.
Serve with cornbread.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Do not add salt!

title: canned peppers
directions: Use large jars.
Cut up 2 cloves garlic; place in bottom of jar.
Clean and cut peppers (wear gloves).
Pack firmly in jars. Add 1 teaspoon oregano and 1 teaspoon salt (plain not iodized) and 1/4 cup oil.
Pour 1 cup distilled white vinegar and add the rest with boiled (cooled) water until jar is filled to top.
Seal bottles up good and set them upside down for one day.
Season for two weeks before opening.

title: rice krispie balls
directions: Unwrap caramels and place in microwave-proof bowl.
Add the can of milk; microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir; microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Continue until completely melted.
Dip each marshmallow in caramel mixture, then roll in Rice Krispies.
Place on wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Put in freezer for a few minutes to set.

title: gooey bars
directions: Mix cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg.
Press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top and press into batter with the back of a spoon.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine
first
three
ingredients
and cream together. Add eggs,
one
at a time and blend each time.
Beat last four ingredients alternately beginning and ending with flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion with salt and pepper, then add and simmer the remaining ingredients.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix the margarine, syrup, eggs, sugar, chocolate chips and pecans.
Blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: garden casserole
directions: In large skillet, melt butter and saute onion, pepper and garlic until soft.
Add squash; cook briefly before stirring in tomatoes, corn and seasonings.
Pour into buttered 3-quart casserole dish and add water.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: english bread pudding
directions: Soak crumbs in milk; beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg, vanilla and raisins.
Mix with bread mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Set in pan of hot water and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Knife inserted must come out clean.

title: chex party mix
directions: In small bowl add Lawry's seasoned salt and Lea & Perrins Worcestershire sauce to melted margarine.
Mix well.
Pour Chex cereals, nuts and pretzels into large bag. Pour margarine mixture over cereal in bag.
Shake bag until evenly coated.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in tight container.

title: microwave turtles
directions: Place caramels, milk and butter in 1-quart casserole.
Heat in microwave on medium-high for 4-5 minutes or until caramels are melted.
Arrange pecan halves in groups of three on a buttered baking sheet.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon warm caramel mixture over each group of pecans.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Place chocolate morsels in a 2-cup glass measure.
Heat on medium-high for 5-6 minutes until melted.
Spoon enough chocolate over each caramel to cover.
Allow to cool.
Remove from baking sheet.

title: meatza pie
directions: Place meat, milk, bread crumbs and garlic salt in a 9-inch pie pan and mix together thoroughly.
Pat mixture evenly on bottom and sides of pan.
Spread catsup or tomato paste over meat mixture and arrange mushrooms evenly on top.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese and sprinkle oregano and Parmesan cheese evenly over all. Bake in a very hot oven at 450° for 20 minutes or until cheese is lightly browned.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and boil for 6 minutes.
Put remaining ingredients in large bowl; pour hot mixture over ingredients in bowl.
Beat until chocolate is all melted; pour into a pan.
Let cool.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator next morning; cut into squares.
Store in tin lined with Handi Wrap.

title: dijonnaise potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir in potatoes, celery and onions.
Cover; chill.
Makes 6 cups.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach into bite size pieces.
Layer spinach, eggs, bacon, green onions and peas in a large deep bowl.
Combine with sour cream, mayonnaise (or salad dressing) and seasonings, stirring well.
Spoon evenly over peas, sealing to edge of bowl. Sprinkle with cheese, if desired.
Cover tightly; chill for 8 hours.
Toss gently before serving.
Serves 8.

title: pork chops
directions: Put pork chops in a baking dish; pour sauerkraut over top of pork chops.
Add 1 cup water.
Bake until pork chops are tender.

title: breakfast tacos
directions: Brown sausage; drain and set aside.
In same pan, melt margarine.
Add potatoes, onions and green chili.
Saute until potatoes are done.
Blend milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Add egg mixture and sausage to potatoes.
Cook until eggs are done.
Serve on warm tortillas with hot sauce.

title: macaroni surprise
directions: Cook and rinse macaroni.
Drain pineapple and oranges and refrigerate until next day.
Cook sugar, flour, eggs, salt and juice from pineapple and oranges.
Cook until thick.
Mix into macaroni.
Let set overnight.
Sauce and macaroni will be a solid mass.
Break up and add fruit.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: beef with corn
directions: Put ground beef with tenderizer in pan with oil; fry until cooked.
Drain fat and add onion, corn, tomatoes, salt and pepper. Cook until everything is tender.

title: layered sea salad
directions: Combine dressing and sour cream and mix well.
Combine noodles and parsley; mix lightly.
In 3 1/2-quart serving bowl layer lettuce, cucumber, noodle mixture, celery, tomato and salmon. Serve with dressing mixture.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: butterscotch haystacks
directions: Melt chips on low heat and stir in other ingredients. Place spoonfuls on wax paper or silicone mat. Refrigerate.

title: penuche icing
directions: Melt butter or margarine and brown sugar in a saucepan.
Boil over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm. Gradually add confectioners sugar, beating until thick enough to spread.
If icing becomes too thick to spread, add a little milk or hot water.

title: peanut butter - chocolate squares
directions: Cream together with mixer to very smooth consistency.
Spread about 1/2-inch thick in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Melt 1 package Nestle's or Baker's chocolate chips.
Pour over the top and when it begins to set, smooth with spatula or knife across the top. Let stand until firm and cut in squares to serve.
Tastes like Reese's cups.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise; scoop out centers.
Place squash in baking pan.
Combine apples, nuts, jelly and butter. Fill squash with mixture.
Pour a small amount of boiling water in bottom of pan around squash.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until fork-tender.
Remove foil during last 5 minutes of baking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix together.
Put 2 teaspoons in a cup and pour in hot water.

title: meat loaf
directions: Crush crackers; put in milk.
Soak for 1 minute.
Mix with hamburger and all ingredients.
Shape up and put in long, greased pan.
Put in oven; cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: touchdown chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk, vanilla and salt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts.
Cool 10 to 12 minutes.

title: yankee pot roast(longfellow's trayside, inc., sudbury)
directions: If using salt pork, cook until some fat is extracted, then remove the salt pork.
In a Dutch oven, brown the roast in salt pork or bacon fat.
Put celery stalks, whole carrots, onions and undrained tomatoes around meat.
Sprinkle meat with salt, peppercorns and bay leaf.
Add water; bring to a boil.
Cover; simmer over low heat or in a 350° oven for 2 1/2 hours, or until tender.
Lift out roast; keep it warm.
Strain the cooking stock; discard vegetables.
Skim fat off stock, returning 1/4 cup fat to the Dutch oven.
Stir flour into fat.
Add 4 cups cooking stock; cook and stir until thickened.
Season to taste.
Add vegetables, which have been cooked separately.
Heat through.
Slice the beef and serve with vegetables and gravy.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: oatmeal maple syrup drop cookies
directions: Beat shortening, maple syrup and egg.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add to first mixture alternately with milk. Mix well.
Add raisins, nuts and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 15 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: spinach fondue
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream, blending well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Turn into a baking dish and heat in 350° oven for 30 minutes, until bubbling.
Let stand 5 minutes.	Serve with bread, crackers and vegetables.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all together thoroughly.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and cool in refrigerator overnight.

title: roast pork, stuffed with prunes and apples
directions: Heat butter and oil in skillet.
Add onion, garlic, 1/2 teaspoon rosemary and 1/2 teaspoon thyme.
Saute about 2 minutes. Add next 3 ingredients.
When apples are softened, add prunes. Remove from heat.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Spoon on lightly oiled cookie sheet. Bake in 400° oven until golden brown.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Combine crushed graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine, stirring well.
Press into bottom of pan and about 1-inch up side of the pan.
Use spring-form pan.

title: cookies 'n cream
directions: Crumble cookies and sprinkle in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter and pour over cookies.
Spread ice cream over cookies and dribble fudge topping over this.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Freeze.

title: brides punch
directions: Mix orange juice, lemonade and water; chill.
Pour orange juice mixture into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale; mix.
Place fruit ring in punch.
Yields 24 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip together peanut butter, Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar and mix until thick and smooth.
Pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells and chill.

title: oyster stew
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients except milk.
Heat and simmer until edges of oysters curl (about 10 minutes).
In another saucepan, scald milk.
Add milk to other ingredients and serve. Sprinkle paprika over each serving.
Makes 4 small servings.

title: relish
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients through fine blade.
Add salt.
Mix well and let stand 3 hours or overnight.
Drain well (I drain it overnight).
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; cook 10 minutes or longer until slightly thick.
Makes approximately 9 pints.

title: gourmet chicken
directions: Coat chicken with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown. Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, water, ginger and rosemary and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with 1/2 can of onions.
Cover and bake at 350° for about an hour.
Uncover and sprinkle with remaining onions.
Bake another 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: country fruit cake
directions: In large bowl, cream butter, sugar, and egg yolks.
Add lemon extract.
Mix well.
Gradually add flour.
Fold in fruits and nuts.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold into cake batter and mix well.
Spoon into greased 10 inch tub pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 200°
for 1 1/2 hours.
Increase heat to 250° and bake 1 hour.
Increase heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool completely in pan.
Store in aluminum foil.
May be frozen.

title: mexican mess
directions: Saute meat; do not add salt.
While meat is browning, dip tortillas in enchilada sauce and line in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan with them.

title: traditional scotch shortbread
directions: Sift the dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Mix well with a spoon.
Empty contents onto a flat, dry surface.
Add softened butter and work the butter into the dry ingredients with your hands until it is like putty.
Flatten out with your hands, then roll dough out until it is about 1/2 inch thick.

Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and gently poke the entire surface with a fork all over; bake in a preheated oven at 325° for approximately 15 minutes or until it starts to brown, then reduce the temperature to 300° and bake another 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Slice into 2-inch squares or some semblance thereof and place back into a cooling oven to complete the process.

title: fruit salad(serves 4)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage in a fry skillet, stirring and breaking up large pieces.
Crumble, drain well.
Set aside.
Combine cheese and soup in a heavy Dutch oven until cheese melts.
Add sausage, picante sauce and milk.
Mix well and serve warm.
If dip is too thick, add 1/4 to 1/2 cup of milk or water.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles 10 to 12 minutes.
Stir together noodles, soup, beef and mushrooms.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with saltines.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: potato kugel
directions: Grate vegetables.
Remove and discard liquid.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart uncovered casserole (greased).
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: ham-broccoli casserole
directions: Cut circles out of center of bread and put all aside.
Butter a 3-quart casserole and put extra bread in bottom of casserole. Place bread circles on broccoli, ham and cheese, layering in order given.
Mix milk, eggs, onion flakes and mustard.
Pour over and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: far east dip
directions: Chop the ham. Mix with remaining ingredients until smooth. Good with chips, crackers, or toast rounds.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix
all
the
ingredients
together.
Pour
1/2 of the batter into
Bundt pan.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and 2 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon; sprinkle on top of batter in pan.
Spread remaining batter on
top of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Take out of pans to cool.
Mix milk and pina colada mix.
Poke holes in cake and pour mixture over cake while cake is still warm.
When cool, put together with Cool Whip and coconut.
Keep refrigerated until ready to eat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with bay leaf and garlic clove for 45 minutes. Remove bone from chicken.
Layer chicken, cheese, chips, soups, pepper, onion and tomatoes alternating in casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 30 minutes.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine eggs, bread crumbs, tomato juice, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic.
Stir in ground beef.
On waxed paper or foil, pat meat into shape of a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham slices on top of meat, leaving a small margin around edges. Sprinkle shredded Mozzarella cheese over ham.
Starting from short end, carefully roll up meat, using foil lift and seal edges and ends.
Place roll, seam side down, in baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes; or until done.
Place Mozzarella triangles over top of roll; return to oven for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Fold together and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours before serving.

title: raisin puff cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Cook the raisins in the water over medium heat until the water is absorbed and set aside to cool. Cream the margarine, sugar and eggs. Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt and add to the creamed mixture. Add the cooled raisins and vanilla and mix well. Shape into walnut size balls. Roll each one in granulated sugar. Bake on a greased baking sheet for about 15 minutes. Makes approximately 8 dozen cookies.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Place pecans and butter in heavy, shallow pan, iron skillet or cookie sheet.
Heat in oven until pecans begin to brown, about 1 hour.
Stir often.
Pour out on foil or waxed paper to cool.
Add seasonings to taste.
Place in airtight container.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger and put in a crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients. Dip in and enjoy.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Mix water and lime.
Pour over cucumbers and soak 24 hours. Drain and rinse well.
Soak in clear water for 3 hours.
Drain and cover with other 5 ingredients.
Soak overnight.
Bring to a boil and cook 35 minutes.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to boil.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: pork and cabbage oriental
directions: Saute onion in 3 tablespoons oil until clear; remove. Add meat to oil and brown.
Add soy sauce and simmer for 30 to 60 minutes. Add cabbage and cover.
Stir occasionally and simmer until cabbage is soft, about 30 minutes.
Serve with rice noodles.

title: punch(hot)
directions: Mix together and boil 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: easy beef and noodle soup
directions: Cook beef and onion in 4 qt. dutch oven, stirring frequently until beef is brown.
Drain off fat.
Add next 5 ingredients and heat to boiling stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add noodles, mushrooms and wine.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Stir in parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli, tomato and cheese bake
directions: Steam or boil broccoli (water does not need to be salted). It's better to undercook broccoli then overcook it.
Arrange drained broccoli into buttered 14 x 8 1/2-inch glass casserole dish.
Pour beaten eggs over broccoli.
Pour tomatoes and juice over broccoli and then top with cheese sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese, oregano, salt and pepper over all.	Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until golden and bubbly.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: *Cream of celery soup is also very good.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix together. Chill. Great with veggies.

title: peach cake dessert
directions: Place peaches and juice in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cake mix over fruit.
Pour melted oleo and nuts next.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the ingredients in the order listed.
Let set in refrigerator 8 hours.
Garnish with eggs and bacon.
Serves 8.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, buttermilk and cocoa in heavy pan. Bring to boil and boil 2 minutes full minutes. Remove from heat and stir in oats, peanut butter, vanilla and coconut. Spoon out on wax paper quickly. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter; add flour and sugar.
Add vanilla, buttermilk and eggs.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Mix sugar, flour and juices.
Add pineapple to evenly cover mixture.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers that have been crumbled in stick of melted oleo.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until thick.

title: orange nut butter cake
directions: Cream the butter well. Add sugar, orange rind and vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Blend in marmalade. Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.

Add to creamed mixture alternately with combine orange juice and evaporated milk. Stir in nuts and blend. Pour into buttered 10-inch tube pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack. Serve warm or cold.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Spread beans, ground beef, cheese, avocado dip and sour cream on
a
large
platter
or
a 12-inch pizza plate in even layers in
the order listed. If desired, garnish with chopped green pepper and a fresh red chili pepper.
Serve with tortilla chips. Makes approximately 12 servings.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in boiling water.
Add Seven-Up.
Chill until partially set.
Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Fold pineapple, marshmallows and banana into Jell-O.

title: cranberry nut muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and baking powder. In another bowl, beat eggs.
Add orange juice and oil.
Stir into the dry ingredients, just until moistened (batter will be lumpy). Fold in cranberries and pecans.
Spoon into 12 greased or paper lined muffin cups (cups will be almost full).
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan to cool on a wire rack.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: chocolate pie(baked in crust)
directions: Stir cocoa into sugar.
Combine sugar, Pet milk, vanilla and butter.
Beat egg yolks until creamy; add to sugar and milk mixture.
Beat egg whites; add them.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: moist brownies
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
(This may be put in oven while oven is preheating to 350°.)
Mix rest of ingredients in large bowl.
Pour mixture into pan with melted butter or margarine.
Mix until completely blended.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Glaze while hot with can of ready frosting.

title: mary ann's apple kuchen
directions: Make a crumb topping out of the first 5 ingredients. Reserve 1 cup for later use. Add eggs and milk. Mix well. Grease 1-inch high baking tray or sheet (jelly roll) pan. Place batter on bottom of baking sheet. Layer apples on top in horizontal lines. Sprinkle on crumb topping and cinnamon.

title: microwaved salmon steaks
directions: Place fish steaks in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Brush fish with mustard, juice and dill mixture.
Cover dish with wax paper. Microwave at High power (10) for 6 to 7 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: lace cookies
directions: In a medium sized heavy bottom saucepan, combine the first three ingredients and bring to a boil.
Immediately remove from heat.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In a large stockpot, brown ground beef with onion, celery and mushrooms.
Drain off any fat from heat mixture.
Add all remaining ingredients to the stockpot and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes, or until carrots and potatoes are tender.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain 2 pounds of sausage. Drain and crumble.
Mix eggs and milk.

title: nutty cracker delight
directions: Place crackers in a single layer in a foil lined 15 x 10 x 1 pan.
In a saucepan over medium heat, melt butter and sugar; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Pour evenly over crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Immediately remove from the pan, cutting between crackers if necessary and cool on wire rack.
Store in airtight container.

title: sunday casserole
directions: Place meat in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish; place onion on top of meat.
Mix soup and water and pour over all.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Serve with hot noodles, rice or boiled potatoes.
There will be plenty of flavorful, self made gravy. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix.
Place a layer of crushed potato chips in baking dish, then chicken salad and cover with more chips.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: creamy corn
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk, butter and salt in small pan.
Cool over low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in corn.
Cook until thoroughly heated.

title: quick chili con carne
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, melt the margarine and brown the ground beef, stirring to break up the meat as it cooks.
Add the onions and cloves.
Pour off excess fat.
Add the beans, tomato soup, water, chili powder, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes, covered.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with corn bread or rice.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: graham cracker fun
directions: Spread crackers with peanut butter.
Make a face with M&M's, or just sprinkle with sugar.

title: mushroom chicken surprise
directions: Wash your chicken.
Add your 1 tablespoon margarine to chicken that goes in the skillet.
Season your chicken.
Cover and let it cook or steam until almost done.
You add your onion, bell pepper and your can of mushroom soup.
Let it cook until your meat is done on low.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in pulp.
Cream shortening and sugar; add nuts and raisins to flour.
Beat egg and add to pulp.
Add dry ingredients; stir.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: lower fat cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.
Shape into ball.
Serve with various crackers.
May be made with regular ingredients for those who do not want to lower fat content.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Be sure to use "cake flour".
Mix all; the more you mix the higher the cake.
Pour batter into Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.

title: melting moments
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in small amount of water until water evaporates. Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and cooking oil; mix well. Blend flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla; mix well. Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 25 minutes or until done.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add fruit cocktail.
Put in greased 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and pineapple, then add Cool Whip, marshmallows and pecans.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; set aside 2 tablespoons of juice.
In a medium bowl, mix salmon, egg and onion until sticky.
Stir in flour.
Add baking powder to salmon juice and stir into salmon mixture.
Form into small patties and fry until golden brown in oil.
Serve with ketchup.

title: pasta and fagioli
directions: In a saucepan, fry garlic gently in oil until golden brown; do not overcook!
Add tomato sauce and water (or stock or broth) and simmer 10 minutes.
Add beans.
Stir gently to combine and simmer 10 minutes.
Cook ditalini or pasta al dente (firm but not mushy). Drain and add to bean mixture.
Stir gently to combine; if too thick, add some water in which the pasta was cooked.

title: mushroom caps with cheese
directions: Dip mushroom caps into melted butter.
Fill.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: roast beef dinner
directions: Using a black rod iron skillet preheated, brown outside of roast.
Place pan with roast (fat side up) in a 325° oven and cook: 20 minutes a pound for rare, 25 minutes a pound for medium rare and 30 to 35 minutes a pound for well done.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine first 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer until blended. Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes. Stir in oranges. Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan. Cool on rack completely. Combine pudding mix and pineapple in large bowl.
Mix well. Chill. Fold in whipped topping. Spread frosting between layers, sides and top.
Refrigerate immediately. Store in refrigerator after cutting.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Simmer chicken until tender in water to which salt and celery tops have been added.
Cool chicken in stock.
Remove the skin and cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Saute chopped onion in 3 tablespoons oil until soft.
Add garlic, chilies, sugar, tomato puree, pepper and chicken.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Melt red hots in the Coke.
Remove from stove and add Jell-O. Stir until dissolved.
Add the can of applesauce.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: cocktail pizza
directions: Grind salami, cheeses, olives and mushrooms coarsely.
Add oil and seasonings.
Mix well and spread on party rye.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Mixture freezes well in plastic container.

title: challah(braided egg bread)
directions: Measure very warm water into large mixing bowl and add yeast. Set aside for approximately 5 minutes until yeast "proofs" (bubbles/foams).

title: soda cracker cheese cake
directions: Mix crushed crackers or pretzels with oleo and sugar; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar well. Add Cool Whip and beat until fluffy.
Spread over cracker mixture. Spread pie filling over mixture.
Refrigerate for several hours. Use raspberry, cherry or blueberry pie filling.
Sprinkle crushed graham crackers or any sprinkle desired.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together into a large mixing bowl. Make a well in the center.
Add water, eggs, oil and pumpkin; blend well.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour batter into a greased 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and carrots.
In a separate bowl beat eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and cinnamon.
Combine all ingredients and pour into two greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes until top is slightly browned around edges.

title: chourice rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Divide dough into 6 balls.
Flatten each ball into a circle, about 6 inches round. Put about 2 tablespoons chourice in center; bring up edges together and seal.
Roll into an oblong.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake 30 minutes until nicely browned.
Remove from oven and brush immediately with margarine.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Beat egg yolks until smooth and creamy, adding the salt.
Melt butter in small saucepan with a pouring lip.
Drop by drop, add 1/2 the butter to the egg yolks and continue beating. Alternately add butter and lemon juice, still beating, until all is used.
Season with some white pepper.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix by hand the flour and sugar.
Bring to a boil the margarine, water, oil and cocoa.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Mix together thoroughly grated cheese, sausage and Bisquick. Mixture will be very stiff and should be kneaded well.
Set aside. Slit and seed the peppers.
If you prefer mild peppers, rinse seeded peppers under running water.
Stuff each pepper with a sliver of cheese.
Pinch the pepper closed around the cheese. Pinch off a bit of the cheese-sausage mixture and pat into a pancake about 1/4-inch thick.
Place the cheese stuffed pepper in the center of the pancake and wrap the pepper completely with dough.
Be sure all edges and ends are sealed.
Roll the dough covered pepper back and forth in your hands to mold into an egg shape.
Roll each "egg" in Shake 'n Bake until coated.
Dip these into the beaten egg and return to the Shake 'n Bake.
Coat the "egg" well.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Boil water and margarine. Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, and flour.
Mix well. Spread over bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: chop suey
directions: Dip meat in flour, brown in large skillet in oil.
Add all ingredients but the bean sprouts and water chestnuts.
Simmer on low heat until done.
About 1 hour 15 minutes.
Add bean sprouts and chestnuts heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice or chop suey noodles or both.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Have margarine, eggs and cream cheese at room temperature. Cream together margarine, sugar and cream cheese.
Add salt and vanilla and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in flour.

title: chocolate microwave fudge
directions: Stir together in 1 1/2-quart dish.
Top with butter and microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Place in buttered dish to set.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple raspberry crumble
directions: Peel apples and cut into 8 or 10 slices each.
Sprinkle lemon juice over apples.
Arrange apples in greased 10 x 6-inch pan or 8 x 8-inch pan.
Drain the frozen berries.
Save juice for other use.
Spread berries over apples.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: grandma lawson's hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine and mix all dry ingredients (everything). Store in sealed container(s) at room temperature.

title: dena's homemade rolls(indescribably delicious)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add boiling water.
Let cool.
Add eggs.
Dissolve yeast in cold water.
Add flour and salt. Refrigerate overnight.
Shape and let rise for 2 hours afterward (pinch and roll into long rope; tie in knot or figure 8 or shape to suit).
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: rice-chicken casserole
directions: Prepare rice.
Cook onions and celery in butter until tender, not brown.
Add all ingredients to cooked rice.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes uncovered.
Garnish with parsley.
Use 7 1/2 x 12-inch dish.

title: one-bowl brownies
directions: Mix by hand.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Divide popcorn between 2 ungreased baking pans, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
In saucepan, heat sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt, stirring occasionally, on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in soda
until foamy.
Pour over popcorn, stirring until corn is well coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain
beans and place in baking dish.
Mix in mushroom soup (do not add water) and 1/2 container of sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with onion rings and brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump cake mix into a bowl. Mix the Jell-O in 2/3 cup water and add to cake mix. Add remaining ingredients and bake 45 minutes in a tube pan at 350°.

title: cheese cake(light)
directions: Chill milk until very cold.
Mix water and jello and let get syrupy.
Beat the can of milk like whipped cream.
Beat cream cheese with 1 cup sugar.
Combine jello, whipped milk and cream cheese mixture.
Pour in prepared graham cracker crust and sprinkle a few cracker crumbs on top.
Refrigerate or freeze until time to use.

title: squash bread
directions: Beat
eggs and sugar until light.
Add oil and vanilla. Stir in	squash	and dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake in 350° for 1 hour.

title: short cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar, add the rest of the ingredients.
Do not roll.
Pat into a 8 or 9 inch square baking pan and bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon-cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water; set aside to cool.
Stir the next 3 ingredients into the cooled Jell-O.
Stir remaining ingredients together and add to slightly set Jell-O mixture.

title: rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in saucepan.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into dessert dishes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: midwest tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients into a bowl; mix well.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except brown sugar, catsup, nutmeg and dry mustard, thoroughly and place in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine brown sugar, catsup, nutmeg and dry mustard; pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: strawberry pineapple pie
directions: Blend milk and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip.
Drain pineapple. Add pineapple, strawberries and nuts to Cool Whip mixture and pour into pie crusts.
Chill.

title: sophisticated meat balls
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients into 16 balls.
Brown in fryer and drain.
Mix together soup, cheese and water.
Pour over meat and simmer.
Serve over noodles.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: tangy meat loaf
directions: Combine catsup, brown sugar and dry mustard.
Remove 4 teaspoons of mixture for topping.
To remaining mixture add Worcestershire, garlic and onion powder, salt, pepper and egg. Blend well.
Stir in green pepper and Chex.
Add beef and mix well. Shape in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.
Remove and spread remaining on top.
Bake 15 more minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pare apples and cut in small pieces.
Add 1 cup water to apples in baking dish.
Combine sugar, flour, butter and vanilla. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in slow oven about 50 minutes or until juice bubbles around edge and topping is brown.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: grandma's rice pudding
directions: Mix together the milk, rice, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Bake for 2 to 3 hours at 350°.
Stir once in a while.

title: quick turtle soup
directions: Cut parboiled turtle meat into small dice.
Brown slowly in chicken fat or butter.
Add onion and saute slowly over medium heat until onion is soft and yellow.
Add mixture to chicken broth in a soup pot.
Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer gently for 10 minutes.
Serve with a sprinkling of chopped parsley and a slice of lemon floating on top.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk and salt
to boil and boil 5 minutes or to soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, margarine and vanilla.
Beat until it loses its gloss.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: no bake peanut oat cookies
directions: In medium saucepan, mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and butter. Put over medium heat and bring to boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and oats.
Drop by teaspoon into foiled-lined sheet pan.
Let stand until firm and cold. Store airtight.

title: rose pedal rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and Crisco.
Beat in other items.
Spoon into greased muffin tins only 1/3 to 1/2 full. Bake at 400° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen rolls.
This dough will keep 1 week in covered container in refrigerator.

title: pear honey
directions: Mix and
heat the ingredients, stirring thoroughly, to dissolve the sugar.
Boil until thick and clear.
Pack into hot clean jars and process in boiling water for 10 minutes.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, margarine, horseradish, lemon juice, onion, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce until smooth. Then add the crabmeat and chill.
Serve with saltine crackers.

title: sausage-cheese breakfast souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Set aside.
Butter bread and place in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish, buttered side down.
Layer sausage, then cheese over bread. Combine remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour over the sausage and cheese; refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: wild duck
directions: Mix this together and stuff duck.
Cover with another can of sauerkraut.
Bake until done at 350°.
Serve with mashed potatoes. Use more sausage and rice if using a larger duck or goose.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add 1/2 cup tomato sauce and taco mix.
Add amount of water stated on taco mix directions.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine sour cream and cream cheese in small bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Spread mixture into 8-inch circle on large platter. Spread taco sauce over cream cheese mixture.
Layer with lettuce, pepper, onion, Cheddar cheese and Monterey Jack cheese.
Sprinkle tomato over top.
Refrigerate, covered, up to 1 hour.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Make 8 to 10 servings.

title: pot roast
directions: Need large cooking bag.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add beaten eggs; mix well. Put bananas through sieve.
Add lemon juice, then add to creamed mixture.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together; mix quickly with banana mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake for about 1 hour at 375°.

title: meat balls and cabbage
directions: Make meat balls.
Line bottom of big pan with half of cabbage. Cut up celery and onions.
Put on top of cabbage, then add meat balls on top.
Then add rest of cabbage.
Then add chopped tomatoes.
Add brown sugar, vinegar and soy sauce, then add bouillon cubes in a circle around pan.
Never stir, always shake the pan.
Start cooking on high for 5 minutes.
Turn down to medium.
When meat balls come to the top it's done.

title: chi alpha hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large container.
Use 1/4 cup per 6 ounces water.

title: pickled blackberries
directions: Wash and pick over blackberries; set aside.
In a small enamel or stainless steel saucepan, add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Remove bay leaf.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into deep dish shell. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°
or until set and knife comes out clean.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook rice with water according to package.
Brown sausage with onion.
Drain.
Mix with rice and pimento.
Pour into baking dish. Pour broth over and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook lasagna noodles as label directs. Drain and set aside.

title: potato salad(greek)
directions: Boil the potatoes in their skins until tender. Drain, peel and cut in uneven chunks.
Place in a large bowl. Add chopped eggs and onion. While still warm, add olive oil, vinegar, oregano, salt and pepper. Toss to coat entire dish.
More olive oil may be added. Entire salad should be moist.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened canned milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon brand lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with pie filling.

title: no-bake cheesecake pie
directions: In a saucepan, melt the white chocolate chips over medium-low heat; stir until smooth. Remove from the heat; stir in cream cheese until smooth. Fold in whipped topping. Pour into graham cracker crust. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Just before serving, sprinkle with toffee bits.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Rinse wild rice and drain.
Mix rice, onion, water chestnuts and mushrooms in a 2-quart casserole.
Add broth and butter. Cover and bake at 325° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: betty's raisin bread
directions: Bake in 2 loaf pans.

title: cheesy vegetable chowder
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large pot.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add corn.
Melt butter in a saucepan, add flour and stir until smooth, gradually add milk and cook until thickened. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook until cheese melts.
Gradually stir cheese mixture into vegetable mixture. Cook until thoroughly heated.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Prepare corn bread mix according to directions.
Stir in corn, cheese, onion and green chilies.
To the browned ground beef, add chili seasoning, tomato sauce and beans.
Simmer for 5 minutes over medium heat.

title: oven baked beans
directions: Spray casserole dish with a nonstick spray; pour in 1 can beans.
Sprinkle with dry mustard.
Add ketchup and dark Karo syrup.
Pour in second can of beans and repeat process (add brown sugar to each layer as well).
Slice bacon into 1-inch pieces; lay across top layer of beans.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours, uncovered.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except the flour and nuts.
Add these slowly and blend.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 minutes in a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Check for doneness with toothpick.

title: kraut 'n pork chops
directions: Season pork chops; brown lightly on both sides.
Stir in sauerkraut into tomato juice.
Arrange a mound of kraut on top of each chop.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon brown sugar.
Cover; cook slowly on top of stove for 40 to 50 minutes or until chops are tender.
Baste with tomato juice several times while cooking.

title: pink popcorn balls
directions: Cook to hard ball stage.
Use butter or cold water to form balls.
Pop 1/2 pound of corn.
Use as little oil to pop, as possible.
Makes 30 to 35 balls.
Wrap in plastic wrap.

title: cheese chess bars
directions: Mix cake
mix, butter and 1 egg thoroughly and pat into a
9-inch cake pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken divan(serves 6)
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling, salted water; drain well.
Cook chicken breasts; bone and skin.
Reserve broth.
Melt butter; blend in flour, salt and a dash of pepper.
Add chicken broth all at once.
Cook and stir until thickens and bubbles.
Stir in cream and sherry.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Self-rising flour may be substituted for the plain flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together the first 5 ingredients until creamy.
Sift together the remaining ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: "you name it" stew
directions: Brown and drain meat in large skillet.
Drain liquid from corn and mix in skillet along with the beans and stewed tomatoes. Simmer until heated throughout.
Serve with hot cornbread for a very quick and easy meal!

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container in dry place.
Use 1/3 cup of mix to 1 cup hot water.
For variety, instant coffee or a dash of cinnamon may be added to dry mix.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add cheese and pineapple (not drained). Mix well.
Put in greased casserole dish.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients as listed and bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Cool and peel.
Cut into cubes (or mash).
Add remaining ingredients.
More mayonnaise may be added to achieve desired consistency.
Chill for about 1 hour.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Cook onion in oil until brown.
Add finely broken ground chuck and cook until well done.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add onion, celery, salt, pepper and sage.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add bread crumbs and poultry seasoning.
Toss until well blended.
Stuff turkey.

title: potato casserole
directions: Stir together in a large bowl; top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carolyn's shrimp toast
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Spread on each half of split English muffins.
Cut each English muffin half into 4 pieces.
Freeze on cookie sheet, then store in a zip-lock freezer bag until ready to cook.
Bake at 425 degrees for 10-15 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Rub 10 x 2-inch baking dish with cut garlic and 1 tablespoon butter.
Peel potatoes; slice 1/8-inch thick. Place in cold water. Drain and dry potatoes when ready to use.
Spread half in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle over them 2 tablespoons butter, 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper and 1/2 cup cheese. Arrange remaining potatoes over top. Spread rest of butter, salt, pepper and cheese over second layer.
Pour on milk over all.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender, milk has been absorbed and top is nicely browned.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add sugar, cold water and pineapple juice.
Freeze in gallon size Ziploc freezer bags. Thaw 1 hour before serving.
Add 7-Up and more pineapple juice, if desired.
Makes 30 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: pie crust for pot pie
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening. Beat egg slightly; add water and vinegar to egg. Add egg mixture gradually to dry ingredients; mix just enough to hold dough together.

title: brownies
directions: Blend melted butter, sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Add eggs; beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to egg mixture until well blended. Spread in greased 8-inch square pan or 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from edges of pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour over pancakes and roll, if desired.

title: praline-pumpkin dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease bottom and sides of 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Beat pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar and pumpkin pie spice in medium bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Pour into pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts. Pour melted butter evenly over top of dessert.
Bake 50-60 min. or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool slightly. To serve cut dessert into 4 rows by 3 rows.
Serve warm or chilled with dollop of whipped cream sprinkled with pumpkin pie spice. Store covered in refrigerator.
Yield:
12 servings.
High altitude (3500-6500 ft.) heat oven to 375 degrees and bake 55-65 min.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam and drain broccoli.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients in order.
Toss and top with 3/4 cup Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy man's lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown beef and drain.
Add soup, puree and simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook noodles.
In a baking dish, layer noodles, meat and cheese 3 times.
Bake uncovered for 15 minutes. Serves 12.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients, blending well.
Shape into loaf. Spread 1/3 cup catsup on top of loaf.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hobnails
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add a little at a time and beat well.
Fold in raisins.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan delight tarts
directions: Cream
margarine with cream cheese, adding flour.
Place dough in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: hot sausage soup
directions: Fry celery, onions and sausage in small amount of oil.
Cut sausage into 1/2-inch pieces. Put all ingredients into large pan and simmer for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation Time: 1:00.

title: calamondin cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients
together at one time for 5 minutes.
Bake in Bundt pan or tube pan for 45 to 50 minutes. Generously grease Bundt pan and/or tube pan before putting in mixture.
After 10 minutes of standing after baking, while still hot, mix and pour over xxxx sugar, calamondin pulp and lemon extract or lemon juice.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix well all ingredients in bowl.
Add chicken breasts.
Let stand 1 hour in refrigerator or as long as you want, but at least one hour.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes.

title: mustard marinade sauce
directions: Mix all the ingredients, add spices to taste.
Marinate chicken, then place chicken and marinade in frying pan.
Cook over medium heat.

title: fried poke stalks
directions: Clean poke stalks from poke salate.
Slice in small round pieces.
Dip pieces in flour, meal mixture.
Heat oil in skillet. Fry poke stalks until good and brown.
Drain all grease off.
Eat and enjoy.
Tastes like fried okra.

title: breakfast hominy
directions: Beat eggs and milk; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into well buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour, until custard is set and golden brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 50 to 60 minutes in 2 loaf pans in a 350° oven.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together, then add remaining ingredients.
Beat all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour in greased loaf pan.

title: weight watchers spanish rice
directions: Cook all but the cauliflower until thick.
Separately cook and mash cauliflower.
Combine cauliflower and sauce and put in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cherry fluff salad
directions: Beat together milk and Cool Whip.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and chill.
Low cholesterol.

title: teresa's french toast - strawberry
directions: Soften cream cheese; spread on 2 slices of bread.
Spread with strawberry preserves; put together like a sandwich.
Mix milk and egg; dip sandwich in egg mixture.
Fry in a nonstick skillet with butter or Pam.
When light brown or crispy, it is done.
Put on a plate; sprinkle with confectioners sugar before serving.

title: italian sausage and tortellini soup
directions: Saute sausage in heavy Dutch onion over medium-high heat until cooked through.
Using slotted spoon, transfer to large bowl.
Pour off all but 1 Tbsp. drippings.
Add onion and garlic and saute until translucent.
Return sausage to pan.
Add stock, tomatoes, tomato sauce, zucchini, carrot, bell pepper, wine, basil and oregano.
Simmer until vegetables are tender, about 40 minutes.

title: easter fruit and nut bread
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups of flour and yeast.
Heat milk, 1/4 cup sugar, butter, lemon peel, 1/2 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt just until warm (115° to 120°).
Stir constantly; add to flour mixture and yolks and 1 whole egg.
Beat with electric mixer on low speed 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed. Using a spoon, stir in as much of the remaining flour as you can. Turn out onto floured surface; knead in enough remaining flour to make a moderately soft dough.
Shape into a ball; place in greased bowl and turn once.
Cover; let rise until double.
Punch down; let rest 10 minutes.
Divide dough into sixths.
Combine walnuts, the 1/3 cup sugar, egg whites and lemon juice; set aside.
Beat remaining egg and 1 tablespoon water; set aside.
Roll each sixth of dough into a 10 x 14-inch rectangle.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt into bowl. Combine egg, milk and oil. Add to dry ingredients. Beat with rotary beater until dry ingredients are just moistened. Do not overbeat. Stir in oats. Bake in preheated waffle iron until steam stops and waffles are golden brown.

title: fried soft crabs
directions: After cleaning crabs, season with salt and pepper, dust with flour.
Fry in hot oil until crispy.

title: greek bread
directions: Melt butter.
Add remaining five ingredients.
Mix well. Season with garlic salt.
Chill for several hours.
Cut French bread and spread with mixture.
Cook at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: microwave chocolate oat snack cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed until creamy.
Stir in 1 cup chips. Spread batter into 8-inch square microwavable dish.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/4 turn. Microwave on High an additional 4 to 5 minutes or until top appears dry.
Sprinkle remaining chips over top of warm cake.
Let stand 10 minutes; spread over cake and cool.

title: maple flavored syrup
directions: Combine sugar and water; stir until dissolved.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, then boil gently for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat. Cool slightly and add flavorings.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Place fruit in 2 qt. casserole, sprinkle with brown sugar. With fork mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add egg to dry ingredients and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grandma's ginger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill dough as it will roll easier. May need to add flour as you roll out dough.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 365° for 6 to 7 minutes.
These are chewy.

title: coconut fruit cake
directions: Mix ingredients and add milk. Mix well!
Grease tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dilled salmon pasta salad
directions: Put cooked pasta into a large bowl.
Add salmon, frozen peas, and green onions.
In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise, yogurt, and dill. Pour over the pasta mixture and toss gently to combine. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Chill at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: club salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with lettuce or fruit.

title: american dream frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk, beating until smooth, thick and stiff (I use whisk). Set aside to cool.
Beat remaining until fluffy, then mix in the flour mixture on slow until well mixed. Excellent on strawberry or chocolate cake.

title: salad
directions: Mix and let set.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish; top each with a slice of lemon.
Sprinkle each chop with 1 tablespoon brown sugar.
Dilute soup with water; pour over chops.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: rickshaw carrots
directions: Combine tomato soup, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
Heat sauce until almost boiling; simmer for a few minutes.
Pour over carrots.
Marinate at least 2 hours.
May be prepared the day before.
Reheat before serving.

title: scramble
directions: Put all cereals in a large heavy (new, clean) trash bag.
Mix liquids and salts in a 4-cup measuring cup, stirring well.
Pour oil mixture over cereals and shake well to coat.
Pour mixture into a large aluminum pan and bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool on paper towels and store in airtight containers.

title: avocado cocktail spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well, cover and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: louisiana jambalaya
directions: NOTE:
This is a very hot, spicy dish!

title: sicilian ricotta cheesecake
directions: Set rack in middle of oven.
Butter and flour a 9 1/2-inch spring-form pan (tap out excess flour).
Mix graham cracker crumbs, walnuts, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and melted butter together.
Press in sides and bottom of pan.

title: apple strudel
directions: In a saucepan, combine apples, brandy, raisins, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.

Add a little water to cook over low heat, steaming apples. Cook apples until they are tender but not mushy. Mix the cornstarch or flour with the lemon juice and add to apples. Cook until liquid is clear.
Set aside to cool.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Grate corn off cob.
Add egg yolks to milk and blend.
Whip whites of eggs until stiff.
Blend grated corn, egg and milk, salt and flour.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into buttered casserole. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: szechwan eggplant
directions: Rinse eggplants and cut off caps, but do not peel.
Cut into 1-inch chunks and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Add 1/2 cup broth and cover with lid or plastic wrap.
Stirring midway through cooking, microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender. Place peanut oil in a 2-cup glass measure.
Add garlic and ginger root.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds.
Stir in sugar and cornstarch.
Blend in remaining 2 tablespoons broth, hot bean sauce, soy sauce, sherry, vinegar and sesame oil.
Microwave on High for 30 to 60 seconds or until slightly thickened.

title: hawaiian stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Prepare oven at 400°.
Mix hot water and margarine in bowl. Stir in stuffing mix, pepper and 1/2 of the pineapple with syrup. Beat out the chicken breasts flat.
Spoon stuffing on chicken and roll tightly and hold with toothpicks.
Place in a 9-inch square baking dish with extra stuffing in center.
Mix remaining pineapple, syrup, sugar, vinegar and ginger.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes or until thoroughly done.

title: skinny cheese pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; add boiling water.
Stir in blender a few seconds; add Alba and cheese; stir.
Add sweetener and extract; blend together.
Add 5 to 6 ice cubes one at a time at high speed.
Pour into pie pan and freeze 5 minutes.
Spread with chilled, crushed, sugarless pineapple.

title: creamy salmon quiche
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry. Drain salmon, reserving the liquid, and sprinkle salmon chunks over the bottom of pastry. Combine the cream cheese and lemon juice.
Gradually beat in reserved salmon liquid, salt and cream.
Beat egg yolk and cheese mixture. Spoon over the salmon in the pastry lined pan. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes or until top is lightly browned and the filling is set.
Garnish with pimiento "fish."
Serve hot in wedges to 6.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cake mix with 2 eggs and melted oleo.
Spread mixture into buttered and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar. Spread over the top of the first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish or baking pan, layer lettuce, celery, onion and green pepper.
Layer of frozen peas is added last.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar in small bowl.
Spread over layers.
Top with shredded Cheddar and bacon bits.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix everything except poppy seed.
Blend 4 minutes at medium speed.
Fold in seed.
Pour into greased pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: hunter's squirrel gumbo
directions: Clean and wash squirrels thoroughly.
Cut into serving pieces and dredge well with mixture of flour, salt and black pepper. Brown well in heavy skillet with oil (iron skillet is excellent). Remove squirrels.
Add flour to make roux.
Add water; stir well (enough water for thin broth).
Add onions, enough chopped celery to taste (approximately 1 stalk), okra, salt and pepper.
Place squirrels back in skillet; bring to boil.
Reduce heat to very low, cover and cook until meat falls off bone.
File may be added before serving, but okra serves some purpose.
Serve over hot rice.

title: amish noodles
directions: Make a well in flour. Add salt, egg, oil and water. Make a ball after kneading 5 minutes; let rest 45 minutes. Cut in half. Roll out each to 8 x 14-inches. Let dry 3 to 4 hours.
Roll up like jelly roll. Cut thin or thick. Let dry several hours.

title: old-fashion sweet dough pies
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, Crisco and butter until creamy.
Add milk. Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture; mix well.
Add more flour until dough is right to roll.
Put in refrigerator and let it cool for 1 hour.
Break dough in small pieces and roll flat. Add fruit filling; fold over and seal edges.
Bake at 350° until brown, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Thaw and drain clams, reserving liquid.
Fry bacon until crisp. Remove bacon and drain.
Saute onion and celery in bacon fat.
Add water to reserved clam liquid to make 2 cups.
Add potatoes, water and clam liquid and seasonings to sauteed vegies.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add clams, evaporated milk and bacon.
Heat through.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley flakes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mom's barbecue
directions: Cook the roast in a crock-pot with the chicken broth overnight.
Drain the meat.
Pull apart in bite size pieces, discarding any fat.
Place in a pot or dish and add your favorite barbecue sauce to flavor the cooked roast, mixing well.
Serve on buns.

title: chicken with snow peas(serves 4)
directions: CONVENTIONAL:
In small cup, combine cornstarch, water, soy sauce, sherry, sugar and seasonings.
In large frying pan, heat oil until very hot.
Add chicken and green onion.
Reduce heat.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is white and done.
Add vegetables and soy sauce mixture.
Cook on simmer setting, stirring occasionally, until mixture has thickened.
Pea pods should be hot, but still crisp.
Serve over fluffy white rice.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix flour, sugar, pecans, and margarine. Press or pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°; let cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, and vanilla.
When mixture is smooth, add half of the Cool Whip.
Spread over the crust. Mix chocolate pudding with half of the milk.
Set aside.
Mix vanilla pudding with the remainder of the milk.
Spread chocolate pudding over cream cheese filling.
Spread vanilla pudding over the chocolate.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.

title: sour cream banana bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan.
Mix sugar, sour cream, margarine and eggs in a large bowl on low speed for 1 minute.
Beat bananas and vanilla into mixture.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Beat for 1 minute.
Stir in nuts.
Spread dough in pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Browned Butter Frosting.
Cut into squares.

title: peppered rib-eye of beef
directions: Trim fat from beef.
Sprinkle pepper and cardamon seed over beef; press in with heel of hand.
Place beef in close-fitting dish.
Mix tomato paste with soy sauce; add garlic powder, paprika and vinegar.
Pour over beef; marinate overnight.
Remove beef, reserving marinade.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Place in pan; let stand at room temperature for one hour.
Bake in 300°
oven for about 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Remove beef from oven.
Combine 1 cup water, 1 cup pan juices and small amount reserved marinade; pour into saucepan.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup water; stir into pan juices mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Slice thin; serve with gravy.
Serves 10.

title: creamy scrambled eggs
directions: Mix eggs and cream cheese.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Pour egg mixture into skillet.
Cook as directed in Home-Style Scrambled Eggs.
Just before eggs are thickened throughout but still moist, stir in bacon.
Sprinkle with chives.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spinach quiche appetizer
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Drain spinach and squeeze out excess water. Add other ingredients. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Cut in small squares.
Serve hot.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: Cook meat in 3/4 of a large pot of water with salt, pepper and celery for about an hour.
Add barley, turnip and carrots.
Cook for another hour.
Add beans, cabbage, potatoes, tomatoes and pot herb.
Continue cooking for another hour.
Add peas and lima beans after 1/2 hour.
Add corn and macaroni and cook until soft.

title: gumbo file
directions: Fry chicken until partially done.
Add sausage, crab meat, onions, garlic, green peppers and parsley.
Fry for 2 minutes.
Add flour and brown.
Add water, tomatoes and sugar; boil for 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 10 minutes.
Add oysters and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add file and keep top off pot until served.
Serve over rice.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel and slice eggplant (oval or round shape). Season with Tony's, MSG and garlic powder. Mix flour and milk together to make batter. Dip eggplant into batter and deep-fry until golden brown.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter, add other ingredients.
Cook until tender.
Pour in casserole dish.
Combine with 1/2 cup grated Swiss cheese, 1/4 cup dry bread crumbs mixed with 2 teaspoons butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: portabello pasta salad
directions: Marinate washed and patted dry mushrooms in balsamic vinegar for about an hour. While cooking pasta, grill mushrooms.
Drain pasta and mix with olive oil, cheese, pepper, and chopped mushrooms.

title: stew beef - baked
directions: Put beef in baking dish.
Sprinkle dry onion mix over top. Top with golden
mushroom soup.
Cover with lid and bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Using a large covered baking dish, salt and pepper as you layer.
Place hash browns in bottom.
Next, layer cheese and onions.
Last, potato chips and also on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: corn dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill overnight. Serve with Fritos.

title: brown sugar chess pie
directions: Mix flour with	sugars.
Add
eggs,
milk
and vanilla. Mix well.
Add	margarine.
Pour
into	unbaked
pie shell and bake in a 325° oven
for 30 to 35 minutes.	Top with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: chicken ole
directions: Combine salsa, mustard and lime juice.
In large bowl, add chicken, turning to coat.
Cover and marinate at least 30 minutes in refrigerator.
Melt margarine in large skillet.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Reserve marinade.
Add chicken to skillet.
Cook until brown on both sides.
Cover.
Let simmer 15 minutes or until no longer pink.
Add reserved marinade and cook until chicken is tender and glazed.
Contains 194 calories and 8 g fat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate coating
directions: Melt chocolate bits and wax in double boiler.
Dip eggs into chocolate mixture with a fork and put on wax paper.
Put nut on top.

title: walnut cream roll
directions: Beat whites with salt and vanilla until soft peaks form. Gradually beat in sugar. Beat yolks until thick and lemon-colored. Fold yolks into whites; carefully fold in flour and nuts. Line bottom and sides of 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with waxed paper. Spread batter evenly in pan. Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 12 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched. Cool 5 minutes. Loosen sides of cake; turn out onto towel sprinkled with sifted confectioners sugar. Peel off paper. Cool to lukewarm. Starting at narrow end, roll cake and towel together. Cool on rack. Unroll; spread with whipped cream. Reroll cake; chill.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each addition.
Add lemon juice and almond extract; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Bake in waxed paper lined 5 x 10-inch loaf pan at 325° for 70 minutes.

title: peter pan crunch clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and add peanut butter.
Stir in peanuts. Drop by spoonful into paper candy cups and chill.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: cream of pumpkin soup
directions: Note:
Any dark orange winter squash may be used instead of pumpkin.

title: seafood stir-fry
directions: Heat oil.
Add crab and vegetables.
Stir over medium high heat for 2 minutes.
Add seasoning.
Cook 1 minute.
Garnish with chow mein noodles.
Serves 4.

title: pork chops in sherry
directions: Salt and pepper chops and lightly brown on both sides.
Place in baking dish and pour over the mixture of sherry and sour cream. Cover and bake in 350° oven for an hour.
Yields 4 to 6 servings, depending on number of chops used.

title: low-fat nutty pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder.
In large mixing bowl add beaten eggs, sweetener, pumpkin, pineapple and juice.
Mix well; then add half the dry ingredients, mix again and gradually add the rest of dry ingredients, mix well. Then fold in Grape-Nuts cereal. Spray well a Bundt pan or 2 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done when tester comes out clean when inserted in center.

title: chicken and taco chips casserole
directions: Cook's note:
Casserole freezes well.
Also, to save time, in the morning I put the chicken in a crock pot with the chicken and rice soup and add water as necessary.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix buttermilk, oil and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° approximately 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: salmon and corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the potatoes, onion, celery, chicken broth, garlic and salt.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir in cream, milk and butter.
Combine flour and corn; stir into soup.
Heat, but do not boil, until slightly thickened.
Gently stir in salmon and heat through.
Yields 6 to 8 servings (2 quarts).

title: basic pie crust(for single-crust pie)
directions: Combine flour and salt in medium bowl. Place shortening on top and using pastry blender, cut shortening into flour until particles are about size of small peas or coarse meal. Sprinkle cold water, 1 tablespoon at a time, over flour-shortening mixture, tossing lightly with fork to distribute liquid evenly. Form pastry into ball using hands. Roll out immediately or chill 30 minutes to 2 days. Makes crust for 1 single-crust pie.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Prepare French bread and salad ahead.

title: ghana stuffed crabs (akatonshi)
directions: Put crab meat in boiling salted water along with ginger piece and cloves. Cook about 15 minutes, until meat is tender enough to flake with a fork.
Drain, flake and set aside.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Prepare and measure all ingredients (except Wesson oil) into a large bowl.
Using fingers, mix well.

title: ham and melon
directions: Peel the melon and cut into slivers, removing seeds and fibers.
Arrange the slivers, radiating out from the center of a serving plate.
Sprinkle with pepper.

title: apple cinnamon muffins
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Mix last 3 in a separate bowl, then stir in dry ingredients.
Top with cinnamon-sugar.
Bake in muffin pan at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes. Serve warm.

title: ladies' retreat oriental salad
directions: Pour melted butter over noodles, seeds and almonds and bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Watch carefully so that it does not burn.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Drain and set aside the first 3 ingredients.
Dice and add onion and celery.
Mix together and bring to a boil the remaining ingredients.
Cool and pour over mixed vegies and refrigerate. Make at least 1 or 2 days ahead so it will marinate.
(Diamonds have "Kountry Kist" "Kitchen Cut" green beans cut on an angle that would look pretty, but any cut green beans will be fine.)

title: mississippi fried oysters
directions: Drain oysters and soak in eggs.
Mix corn meal, sugar, salt, pepper and flour.
Dip oysters in corn meal mixture and fry in deep fat until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine and mix first 5 ingredients.
Spread half of mixture in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with chilies and cheese. Spread remaining batter over top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Mix all other ingredients except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 mixture into dish.
Chill firm.
Then spread sour cream onto layer.
Then pour remaining mix onto it.
Chill overnight.

title: seafood delight
directions: Saute onions and garlic in olive oil.
Add scallops and shrimp; cook until shrimp are pink.
Mix all cream ingredients together in separate bowl.
Cook fettucine al dente.
Place fettucine in a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex baking dish and spray with Pam.
Add fish to mixture with pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: granny ruth's skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add sugar, eggs and dates. Cook 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, nuts and cereal.
Mix well and form into balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: pearl's applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and applesauce.
Stir well.
Add flour and spices.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: tutti-frutti bread pudding
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan and put in bread crumbs and set aside.
In mixing bowl, mix all other ingredients and pour over bread crumbs and mix.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and chill for easier handling.
Make into small balls. Bake on cookie sheet in a 400° oven until brown.
It makes about 100 balls.

title: praline sweet potatoes
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, salad dressing, 1/4 c sugar, ginger and orange peel.
Spoon into 1 1/2 quart casserole. Mix remaining 1/4 c sugar, pecans, butter and sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: pickled red beet eggs
directions: Drain all red beet juice.
Measure juice and add same amount of vinegar;
add sugar.
Bring to a boil.
