title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; stir carefully so as not to break carrots. Refrigerate overnight.

title: pork chops with apple stuffing
directions: Combine stuffing mix, 1/2 cup apple juice, butter/margarine and chopped apple in a large bowl.
Saute pork chops in 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat until brown on both sides. Sprinkle with salt and pepper, if desired.
Mound 1/4 of the stuffing mixture on top of each pork chop.
Sprinkle with paprika. Add 1/4 cup apple juice to skillet.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until pork is done and stuffing is heated through.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix first
ingredients
together
in large saucepan. Stir in berries.
Stir
over medium heat until thick.
Combine next 3 ingredients
in another bowl and cut in margarine until crumbly. Combine milk and egg and add to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.	Pour
berry
mixture
in
an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drop
topping
mixture
into
mounds on top and sprinkle with additional sugar.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.	Makes 6 servings.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter together; mix in sugar.
Roll into balls.
Mix melted chips and wax in double boiler; dip balls into chocolate.
Let dry.
Repeat dip.
Refrigerate.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Beat cream cheese with electric beater until well creamed. Add sugar, eggs and vanilla and beat until fluffy, about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Seed, peel and mash avocados.
Peel tomatoes and chop fine. Finely chop onion.
Place all ingredients (except Tabasco) in a blender or food processor and blend until smooth.
Add Tabasco to taste.
Serve with tortilla chips and sour cream or salsa.

title: mamie's fish chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Add onion.
Cook until tender. Add potatoes, water, seasonings and fish.
Cover; cook slowly for 15 to 20 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Blend in milk and butter.
Cook until heated.
Garnish with parsley sprigs.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown together the hamburger and onion.
In a baking dish, layer in this order:
tortillas, hamburger mixture which has been mixed with the sauce, soup, chilies and beans and then the grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Best baked in an iron skillet. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and bring to a rolling boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour over the cherry Jell-O and stir real good to mix.
Take the Coke, pineapple and nuts; mix with Jell-O.
Refrigerate until jelled.
Best to make the day before.
Great with dressing.

title: phyl's onion rings
directions: Mix, let set 1/2 hour.
Using either electric skillet or deep fryer, fry until golden brown.

title: swiss steak(microwave)
directions: Flour meat; salt and pepper meat.
Lay in layers in microwavable bowl.
Mix tomatoes and onions together; pour over steak.
Cook in microwave, turning every 15 minutes.
Will take about 1 hour to cook.
If cooked in oven, don't flour steak. Cook at 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: slaw
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over cabbage and onion.
Set aside for 1 hour.

title: dr. pepper bundt cake
directions: Mix cake and pudding mixes, Dr. Pepper, oil, eggs, and pecans well. Pour in bundt pan. Bake for 50 minutes or golden brown in a 350° oven.

title: ridiculously simple pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add oil, water and then pumpkin. Sift dry ingredients together and add to above.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake in oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 large loaves or 3 small loaves.
Keeps well in fridge or freezer.

title: louisiana shrimp
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Place half shrimp in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Sprinkle half dry mixture over shrimp and pour 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce.
Repeat with second half.
Cut butter into chunks, place on shrimp.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Grill, bake or broil chicken until done.
In a large skillet, heat the other ingredients until boiling.
Add chicken and simmer slowly for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Sauce may be used for other meats as well.)

title: rotel relish
directions: Step 1:
Wash cucumbers.
Slice cucumbers in gallon jar.
Pour 1 1/2 cups of salt over cucumbers in jar.
Add water to cover cucumbers in jar and let stand for 9 days.

title: onion soup canape
directions: Cream onion soup mix and butter. Put on small pieces of French bread or other kinds.
Toast.

title: souffle orange en orange
directions: Orange Pastry Cream:
Boil the orange juice with the skin of one orange.
Mix the egg to the sugar.
Add the flour.
Mix the orange juice to the mixture.

title: country chicken-vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer until noodles are tender.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, onion, eggs, salt and pepper.
Add broccoli.
Place in bottom of baking dish. Cover with grated cheese.
Melt butter and mix in stuffing mix. Place on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit pizza(two crust)
directions: Mix all ingredients (except Cool Whip).
Pat into pizza pan and bake.
Cool.

title: creamy sliced tomatoes
directions: In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, cream and half of the basil; mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in large skillet. Add enough water to mix. Add milk. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Great over hot biscuits.

title: sweet potato or pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well all ingredients, electric mixer does best job.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven until firm or toothpick comes out clean.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: In a heavy-bottomed 2-quart pan, combine first 6 ingredients. Set over medium-low heat and stir frequently with a wire whisk. Boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat and let cool. Add remaining ingredients. Store in refrigerator.

title: easy nachos
directions: Mix nacho soup and Cheddar cheese soup together; melt in saucepan.
Serve over chips and top with jalapeno peppers.

title: favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, gradually adding sugar, beating on medium speed of electric mixer until light
and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add water and
vanilla;
mix well.
Combine flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add
to creamed mixture; mix well. Stir in oats and pecans.

title: corn casserole
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with butter.
Mix all ingredients together and place in dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
May be made night before and refrigerated.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Place onion and 2 tablespoons butter in a small pan. Cook until tender. Stir in flour, salt, mustard and pepper.
Cook for 1 minute. Slowly stir in milk and cook, stirring until smooth.
Add 3/4 of the cheese.
Pour macaroni in a dish.
Pour cheese sauce over macaroni. Top with remaining cheese.
In a pan over low heat, melt 1 tablespoon margarine.
Stir this into the bread crumbs and sprinkle this over the cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: lindsey's favorite pot roast
directions: Put roast in large roaster and put salt, pepper and garlic powder on top to your taste.
Broil until the top sizzles.
Put lid on roaster and cook in 350° oven for 2 to 3 hours, depending on size of roast, along with the soup, soup mix and water.
After cooking, add the remaining ingredients, stir.
Add more water, if needed, to just cover the top of the vegetables.
Bake another 1 1/2 to 3 hours, depending on amount.

title: parmesan onion soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet.
In a large bowl, combine flour, 1/3 cup Parmesan, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and chopped onion. Cut in margarine/butter until crumbly.
Stir in sour cream and milk until just moistened. Turn onto lightly floured surface and knead until smooth (1 minute).
Divide dough into 2 portions.
Shape into round loaves.
Place on greased sheet. Brush tops of loaves with egg white.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese. Cut an "X" about 1/2-inch through top of each loaf.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool on racks. Makes 2 loaves.

title: super good cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar and let stand overnight.

title: pumpkin dish
directions: Beat first 9 ingredients until smooth.
Place in buttered rectangle Pyrex dish.
Top with the next four ingredients for topping.
Sprinkle topping on top of pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hard candy
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water to hard crack stage at 300°. Remove
from
heat	and
stir
in
rest of ingredients, except confectioners
sugar.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on cookie sheet.
Quickly pour mixture onto confectioners sugar. Let	cool completely.
Sprinkle
more
confectioners sugar on top.
Break into bite size pieces.

title: cocktail pork bbq
directions: Combine all ingredients
and simmer 3 hours.
Mash with potato masher; continue cooking until thick as desired.
Serve in chafing dish
with small rolls.
Triple amount for cocktail party.

title: do-nut balls
directions: Cut or tear biscuits into 3 pieces each.
Fry 10 pieces at a time in a preheated Fry Baby or Fry Daddy.
Drain fried biscuits on paper towel.
Shake in a bag with about 1 cup of powdered sugar. Eat while warm.
Remaining powdered sugar may be saved in a Ziploc bag and reused.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup.
Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup water and add to soup.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and pour into mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with crackers, rye krisp or melba toast.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into crust-lined pie plate or quiche pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375° or until knife comes out clean.

title: icebox angel food cake
directions: Dissolve unflavored gelatin in boiling water and add can of frozen orange juice (undiluted).
Let jell.
Whip with vanilla ice cream and coconut.
Put back into refrigerator.

title: dutch lace cookies
directions: Combine molasses, sugar, shortening and vinegar in saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Sift remaining ingredients together.
Add to molasses mixture.
Return to heat; cook until thick, stirring constantly. Drop 1/2 teaspoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet about 3 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 3 to 5 minutes or until slightly browned. Cool slightly before removing from sheet with a greased spatula. Roll slightly for a curly edge.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Beat together and slowly add flour and vanilla.
Beat well.
Use a tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add chicken broth; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and eggs.
Spoon chicken mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cut pastry into 3/4-inch wide strips.
Arrange strips across top of casserole.
Brush pastry with egg.
Bake pie at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: noodle medley
directions: Brown onion, pepper, celery and Vegeburger in margarine. Layer in casserole dish with remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour, until noodles are done.

title: a good rice dish
directions: wash and cook rice, rinse.
Brown beef and mix Taco seasoning, mix rice, salsa, ground beef in pan sprinkle on cheese.
While cheese is browned (melted) remove from oven and garnish with chopped green onions, top & all, and fresh tomatoes.

title: mom's fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter, vanilla and evaporated milk in Dutch oven.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Put 1 can mushroom soup on bottom of baking pan. Put noodles on top of soup.
Crumble chicken on top of noodles. Add olives and mushrooms.
Add remaining 2 cans mushroom soup.
Top with cheese.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle onion rings on top.
Return to oven for about 2 minutes to brown onion rings.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate at least overnight. Excellent served with raw vegetables.

title: jello cake
directions: Prick each cake layer with fork.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Pour carefully over cake layers.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Remove from pans.
Frost top of first layer and stack.
Frost sides and top with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa together. Add beaten egg yolks, milk, vanilla and margarine. Cook until thickened in double boiler. Pour in a baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
Peel.
Place in 5 quart jars.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Heat.
Pour over eggs and cap.
When cool, store in refrigerator.
Store at least 5 days.
The longer they set the better they are.

title: cherry brownie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan on bottom and sides.
Stir brownie mix, pie filling and egg in large bowl until well mixed.
Spread in pan and bake 40 minutes.
When totally cool, frost with icing which has had the almond added to it.

title: apple brownie squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread the batter in a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Sometimes it takes a little longer if the apples are juicy.

title: spinach ring
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Scald milk and blend with eggs. Add salt, Tabasco sauce and butter, stirring until butter melts. Add spinach and mix well.
Turn into a well greased 2 1/2-quart ring mold.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Unmold and fill with Mushrooms A'La Lyonnaise.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Use a glass trifle bowl or any straight sided bowl.
Crumble cake into bottom of bowl.
Layer with 1/2 the mousse, 1/2 the Cool Whip and 1/2 crushed candy.
Add the remaining mousse, Cool Whip and finish with candy.
Chill.

title: tony's souper meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup mushroom soup, onion soup mix, beef, crumbs and egg.
In 2-quart oblong baking dish, firmly shape into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done. Spoon off fat; reserve 1 to 2 tablespoons drippings.
In a 1-quart saucepan, combine remaining mushroom soup, water and reserved drippings.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally. Serves 8.
Serving Suggestions:
Pictured with carrots, sliced new potatoes and parsley.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter in pan; add brown sugar, flour and salt and stir well.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
When mixture gets warm, add small amount to eggs and stir into mixture.
Add vanilla.
Cook until thick.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Discard all but 1 teaspoon fat from skillet.
Add butter, oil and onion.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes or until onion is translucent.
Add broth, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Add cabbage.
Stir over medium-high heat 3 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Stir in bacon, then fold in noodles.
Cook just until noodles are hot.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Prepare
Minute
rice in sufficient quantity to allow 1 cup per
serving.
Brown
sausage
and hamburger in a 12-inch Dutch oven and drain grease.
Add onion and saute until clear. In a separate
pot
combine beans and tomato sauce.
Add meat mixture and
cook
until
hot
over low flame.
Serve meat and bean mixture over bed of rice.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, except water, and beat well at medium speed for two minutes. Stir in boiling water.
Batter is thin.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Divide cake mix in half.
Take 1/2 cake mix and add 1 egg and 1 stick margarine, mix together and pat in sheet cake pan.
Next mix pumpkin pie filling like instructions on can and spread on the first layer.
Mix remaining ingredients together and drop by spoonfuls on second layer.
Bake at 350 degrees 45 to 55 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve with cool whip.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, vanilla and salt together.
Add to beaten eggs.
Pour into uncooked pie shell and sprinkle pecans on top. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy cheese spread
directions: Add mayonnaise as needed to spreading consistency. Use on crackers or great for sandwiches.

title: stuffed beef roulades
directions: Cut steak
into 12 pieces and pound with a meat hammer. Make pieces
long.
Prepare
stuffing
as
directed.
Place 2 tablespoons on
each piece of steak and roll up; fasten with a toothpick.	Brown
in a large skillet in shortening.
Pour off fat.

title: sunset yogurt salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Measure 1 cup gelatin and chill until slightly thickened. Blend in yogurt. Add cold water to remaining gelatin and then add pineapple with juice and carrots. Pour into 5-cup bowl or dish. Chill until set, but not firm. Spoon yogurt mixture over gelatin mixture in dish. Chill until firm, at least 4 hours. Makes 9 servings.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes one large or two small dishes.
Large dish takes approximately 1 hour. Serves 20.

title: honey wheat casserole bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, mix 1/2 cup of the bread flour, all the whole wheat flour and the dry milk, yeast, salt, honey and oil. With mixer on low speed, mix until well blended.
With mixer still going, add the hot water and continue mixing for 3 minutes until smooth.
Add remaining flour gradually, mixing at high speed until dough is smooth.
Put into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with wheat germ over top.
Let rise in warm place until almost doubled, about 45 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add flour, salt, baking soda and nuts.
Lastly, add mashed bananas to mixture.
Grease loaf pan or other desired pan well.
Bake for 1 hour or until done to taste.

title: crock-pot meal
directions: Layer in crock-pot in order listed.
Cook in crock-pot all day.

title: trader vic type chicken(my husband brought this recipe home from friends in toronto.)
directions: Blend marinade ingredients and pour over chicken, coating each piece.
It will smell lovely.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 1/4 hours, basting occasionally.

title: chicken dip
directions: Combine and heat all ingredients.
Serve hot from chafing dish with chips or crackers.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Quarter the potatoes and onion; cook until tender.
Drain only about half the water, then add the milk and spices.
Bring to a low boil, then add the frozen vegetables.
Wait until it starts simmering, then add the cheese.
Let simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes, stirring often, on low heat so it will not burn.
Makes a Dutch oven pot full.
Enjoy.

title: rice dressing
directions: Saut onion in margarine. Place remaining ingredients in large casserole. Stir in sauteed onion. Mix well. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes. Stir well. Cook about 40 minutes longer at 300°. Serve hot with any meat. Serves 6 to 8.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: great grandma harris' potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix potatoes, milk, sugar, margarine, salt and beaten eggs in a mixer and combine well.
Add yeast mixture and again mix well.
Add flour, cup by cup, until the dough is soft, but not too sticky.
Set aside in a greased bowl, in a warm place to rise for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down when doubled.
Let rise again for about 45 minutes, until doubled.

title: tuna and macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Cream the cheese.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well with mixer.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate until firm.
You may serve with blueberry pie filling as a topper.

title: fresh apple butter
directions: Do not core, seed or peel apples.
Just cut into quarters. Cook in enough water to cover for 30 to 35 minutes or until tender.
Put apples and liquid through a sieve or food mill. Measure pulp and for each cup, mix in 1 cup sugar.
Add cinnamon and cloves.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture is thick and smooth (approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours). Pour into hot, clean jars.
Seal and refrigerate.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and Hidden Valley together.
Mix all veggies, salt and pepper together.
After cornbread is cook, cut in half long ways.
Place bottom in serving pan (8 x 12).
Spread with dressing mix.
Add layer of veggie mix.
Add top layer of cornbread.
Add veggie mix.
Add dressing mix.
Top with cheese and bacon bits.
Say the blessing and eat.

title: snowy mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain. Mash potatoes in a large bowl.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic.
Beat at high speed until smooth and light. Stir in chives.
Spoon into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or lightly golden.

title: caramel layer chocolate squares
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Stir until melted.
Set aside.
Combine cake mix, melted butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Stir until mixed.
Press 1/2 of this mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle on top of crust the chocolate chips.
On top of chocolate chips, spread caramel mixture.
Spoon on remaining dough and bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.

title: all-honey cooky
directions: Boil honey and butter for 1 minute.
Cool.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Roll thin; cut and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Place warm water in a bowl.
Add dry milk and mix.
Add sugar; stir until smooth.
If sugar won't dissolve, set bowl in pan of hot water.
Use in recipes calling for sweetened condensed milk.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, oil, water and eggs.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour.
Mix powdered sugar and orange juice to make glaze.
Turn cake onto a plate and dribble with glaze.
Let cool.
This is better on the second day.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Combine and chill.
Can be served with angel food cake.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Whip salad dressing and cocoa.
Sift next 4 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients alternately to cocoa and Miracle Whip mixture with 1 cup water.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cake mix chocolate cookies
directions: Add all ingredients to cake mix.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool on cookie sheet for 10 minutes before removing. Makes 36 cookies.

title: southern meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except tomato sauce and mustard and form into loaf.
Pour tomato sauce into a bowl and using the can as a measure add the same amount of water and mix in the mustard.
Pour over the loaf and bake about 1 hour. This makes six servings and contains about 350 calories per serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Rinse broccoli, cut into bite-size pieces.
Fry bacon until crispy-brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Add to broccoli, stir.
Before serving, add raisins, sunflower seeds and bacon.
Mix well.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Cook all ingredients in 1/2 stick of butter, in a covered frypan for approximately 15 minutes. Place in blender with 1 1/2 sticks of butter until creamy and smooth.
Pour into container and refrigerate overnight. Serve with cocktail rye, crackers and chopped onions.

title: curried bowtie salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix sour cream, and curry powder.
Fold in apple, pineapple, and avocado.
Meanwhile cook pasta in pot of boiling water, salted, until tender (about 5 minutes).
Drain well. Rinse pasta under cold water and drain well.
Fold pasta into sour cream mixture.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: lipton oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In shallow baking pan, thoroughly blend all
ingredients, except potatoes.
Add potatoes and turn to coat
thoroughly. Bake, turning potatoes over halfway through baking time, for 60 minutes or until tender and golden brown. Makes
about
servings.	(Also,	good with mushroom soup mix.)

title: fruit pizza
directions: You will need one throw away foil pizza pan.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Thaw frozen potatoes.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt butter, Velveeta cheese and half and half.
Pour over potatoes. Do not stir.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli, noodles and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion together until tender; drain.
Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Mix together with soup and Cheez Whiz.
Place in casserole dish.
Crumble crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar thoroughly. Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flavorings.
Add soda to flour.
Alternately add flour and sour cream to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and carefully fold into mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake in a preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
It should have a nice brown crust. Turn cake out immediately upon taking it from the oven.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, butter and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Mix 2/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; put in plastic bag.
Quarter biscuits and shake in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Grease a tube pan and place a layer of biscuits.
Pour syrup mixture over and add another layer of biscuits.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Pull apart to eat.

title: meal in a dish
directions: Arrange evenly in a 2-quart baking dish, buttered, the potatoes, adding onion if desired.
Sprinkle with salt, parsley and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly over potatoes.
Decorate top with more catsup if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4.

title: plum nut cake
directions: In a large bowl combine eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift together flour and spices; add to egg mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: dump cake
directions: Place chopped nuts in cake pan.
Pour each remaining ingredient, in order, over chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: orange-cranberry torte(good for thanksgiving or christmas)
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Add dates, walnuts, cranberries and orange rind.
Beat eggs. Add buttermilk and salad oil. Mix well and add to flour mixture.
Mix well and pour into well greased tube pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: diabetic - coconut macaroons
directions: Combine milk and sugar replacement in large bowl, stirring until sugar replacement dissolves.
Add coconut; stir until coconut is completely moistened.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets, 2 to 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until tops are lightly browned.
Remove from pan immediately.
Yields 48 drops.

title: southern pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each egg.
Fold in sifted flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Bake in a slow oven at 350° in a tube pan for 1 hour.

title: arroz con pollo(yellow rice and chicken)
directions: Rinse chicken.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder. In Dutch oven, brown chicken skin side down.
Lower heat.
Add rice and water according to Vigo package directions.
Add onion and some olives and 1/2 of the tomato sauce.
Continue to cook as rice directs until water is absorbed.
Stir up from bottom.
Serve on platter and garnish with olives, pimentos and peas.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender or in a mixer until thoroughly combined and then add nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Fill coffee cans 1/2 full.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: grandma's favorite dog treats
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.

In a large mixing bowl, mix baking powder, garlic powder, flour, yeast and wheat germ. In another bowl, beat eggs and oil together. Gradually add bouillon and egg mixture to dry ingredients. Add cheese.
Mix well. Turn out onto a well floured surface and roll 1/4-inch thick. Cut into strips and then into bite size pieces.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes. Turn out onto waxed paper and let harden overnight.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator or freezer.

title: potato lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in salted water and 1 tablespoon of oil.
Keep in warm water until needed.
Cook potatoes and mash.
Add cottage cheese, egg and salt to taste.
Beat together.
Layer noodles and potato mixture in greased pan, starting with noodles, until all are used up.
Dice onion and saute in butter until soft.
Pour over lasagna.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes until hot.
Cover with foil while baking.

title: egg rolls
directions: When hamburger is 3/4 way done, add cabbage and carrots.
Add all spices.
When completely done, add alfalfa sprouts and broccoli.
Refrigerate until completely done.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add cheese until melted, remove from heat.
In a separate bowl, mix sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Add the butter and cheese mixture.
Mix with the frozen hash browns, spread in a large (9 x 13) casserole dish, slightly dot the top with butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix and chill.
Serves 50 to 60 people.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add green pepper and celery.
Add chicken pieces, soup, cheese and spaghetti.
Add broth and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes and salt until tender.
Drain.
Pour in baking pan.
Mix together rest of ingredients and sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Cover with miniature marshmallows.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Blend sugar, salt and Cocoa.
Stir in beaten eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add milk, margarine, coconut and nuts.
Stir until well blended.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken fricassee with dumplings
directions: Place
chicken	into
quart	Dutch oven.
Add 3 cups water, chopped
onion,
celery,
salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil
over high heat, covered.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered,
40 minutes or until almost tender.
(Remove chicken bones).
Add carrots
and
onions.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Simmer, covered, over low heat for 20 minutes.
Mix the flour
with 1/2 cup cold water, add 1/4 cup hot broth to flour mixture;
stir until
smooth.
Turn
heat to high.
Stir into broth
in Dutch oven.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.	Drop dumplings
over hot chicken and cook as directed. Serves 6.

title: hot chicken salad(1993 taster's luncheon)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Turn into shallow buttered dish. Combine cheese and chips. Sprinkle mixture on top. Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Beat until well blended.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Let it cool for about 30 minutes.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Microwave margarine until liquid. Combine with flour and crushed pecans.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 15 minutes. Remove from oven. Place in refrigerator to chill until firm.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruit and put juice into a heavy 1-quart saucepan.
Add pudding mix and cook until mixture becomes clear. Cool. Add all fruit to sauce when cool.
Fold together and chill.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in microwave until completely melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate mixture until blended.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Mix in flour; stir in nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until a pick comes out clean.
Do not overbake!
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 24 brownies.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup of cold water.
Melt chocolate over hot water.
Scald milk.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Add sugar and cornstarch to egg yolks, mix with scalded milk a little at a time and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and take out one cup of custard.
Blend in the chocolate (melted).
Pour into 9-inch pie shell of crushed graham crackers or gingersnaps and chill.
Dissolve soaked gelatin in the remaining custard when cool, stir in rum flavoring or vanilla.
Beat until well blended the three egg whites with salt and cream of tartar. Beat in gradually 1/4 cup of sugar (just like meringue).
Fold egg whites into remaining custard and pour over chocolate in pie shell. Chill.
Sprinkle top with a little grated chocolate.

title: ham and potato scallop
directions: Cook milk in microwave 2 minutes and set aside.
Cook butter 1 minute; add flour and cook 1 minute.
Briskly stir hot milk mixture, mustard, salt and pepper into butter mixture.
Set aside. Place potatoes into 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Add ham and onion.
Pour sauce over ham and potato mixture.
Cover with wax paper and cook 22 to 24 minutes.
Stir twice.
Sprinkle with cheese and let stand 10 minutes.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots in hot water for 5 minutes (drain).
Cream the shortening, sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients.
Alternate with buttermilk.
Fold in apricots and nuts.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: nut kifles
directions: Cut margarine into flour as for pie dough.
Beat together egg yolks and sour cream and add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Divide dough into 6 pieces.
Wrap in wax paper and chill 6 hours.
Roll each piece on floured board to a 12-inch circle.
Brush with egg white; sprinkle with combined nuts and sugar.
Cut into 12 wedges. Roll from wide end to point; shape into crescents.
Brush again with egg white and nut mixture.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° approximately 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: mounds bars
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat, add milk and sugar gradually.
Add coconut.
Knead with hands.
Form into small bars.
Place on waxed paper and chill 30 minutes.
Dip in melted chocolate.
Can place an almond on top for an "Almond Joy."

title: baked apple french toast
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter; add brown sugar and water. Cook mixture until bubbly, stirring often.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange apple slices over the syrup.
Place bread slices on top of apples in a single layer, covering completely.
Mix eggs, milk, vanilla and cinnamon and pour evenly over bread.
Cover dish with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, preheat oven to 350°.
Remove French toast from refrigerator while oven is heating.
Bake toast, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until puffed and golden.
To serve, cut into 8 pieces and invert onto platter.

title: buttered-pecan ice cream
directions: Saute in pan butter and pecans.
Beat eggs 5 minutes.
Add sugar and beat 5 more minutes.
Add 2 teaspoons or more vanilla extract, syrup, evaporated milk and buttered pecans.
Put in freezer.
Finish filling with whole milk.
Freeze.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, spices and eggs.
Pour into 9 x 11-inch pan.
Pour dry cake mix over mixture.
Put nuts evenly in mix.
Spoon melted margarine evenly over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: triple-decker strawberry cake
directions: Beat cake mix and next 7 ingredients at low speed with an electric mixer 1 minute.
Scrape down sides, and beat at medium speed 2 more minutes, stopping to scrape down sides, if needed. Strawberries should be well blended into batter.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9 inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 23 minutes or until cakes spring back when lightly pressed with finger.
Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely on wire racks.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Combine flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt in bowl.
Cut in margarine until mealy.
Add yogurt.
With flour on fingers, roll into a ball and press into a pie pan.
Press up on sides a little.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well and pour into greased 9 x 9-inch dish.
Combine last 4 ingredients.
Mix together until sugar and cocoa are dissolved. Pour slowly over cake mixture.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook over medium heat for 2 hours.
Put in jars and cook for 1/2 hour.

title: creamy chops and rice
directions: In individual heavy-duty foil packets, place a pork chop, a tablespoon of uncooked rice and about 2 tablespoons of soup. Wrap tightly. Bake in oven preheated to 400° or place about 4-inches from hot coals for 50 to 55 minutes until tender.

title: garden vegetable pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In a medium bowl, thoroughly blend milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper; set aside. Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate. Cook vegetables for about 5 minutes. Drain well. Toss vegetables with cheese and spoon into pie plate. Pour batter over vegetables and bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Drain pineapple; mix well with milk and lemon juice.
Add pecans and Cool Whip and mix until thick.
Pour into pie crusts; refrigerate for at least 6 hours.

title: cheese and bacon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle bacon, onion and cheese in bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting into wedges.
Can be served as an appetizer or a main dish.

title: breakfast granola
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Whiz together in blender the next 5 ingredients.
Add to dry mixture, stirring thoroughly.
Bake at 250°, stirring every 20 minutes for about 1 hour or until brown.
Yields 24 cups.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make shapes with cookie press.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Melt cheese.
Mix hamburger and cheese together and add taco seasoning.

title: grinath lemon cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, adding eggs (one at a time).
Sift and add dry ingredients.
Roll and cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pat's chicken dish
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half.
Pound each to flatten. Roll up and wrap piece of bacon around each piece.
Do not overlap bacon. Use a large baking dish.
Line bottom of baking dish with dried beef.
Lay chicken on top. Combine the sour cream and soup.
Pour over top.
Cook, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar and pineapple; bring to a soft boil in saucepan. Set aside to cool.
When mixture is cool, beat together the cream cheese (softened) and milk in a separate bowl.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions on box and fold into cream cheese mixture. Fold in cooled Jell-O.
Stir well and pour into mold or bowl. This makes a double salad so use a Bundt pan or large bowl.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix vinegar in the milk.
Set aside.
Mix other ingredients. Add milk mixture.
Roll out.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased baking pan. Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: twice baked potato
directions: Bake potato about 40 minutes at 375° until soft.
Cut a cross in the top of each potato so that steam can escape.
Break potato away from skin with a fork, being careful not to scoop out of potato.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Mix into potato.
Add sour cream, chives and grated cheese.
Stir and mix carefully so as not to break the potato skin.
Sprinkle with additional cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes or until cheese melts and begins to brown at edges.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and cook at 350° until brown.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add vanilla, milk and egg; mix well.
Roll in wax paper.
Store in icebox or freezer until ready to bake.

title: almost fat-free cheesecake
directions: Mix together zwieback toast, 4 tablespoons sugar and softened Parkay.
Press into 9-inch spring-form pan (lightly sprayed with fat-free Pam cooking spray).
Set aside.

title: quick cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
(Drain off grease.)
Add taco and enchilada sauces.
Simmer while mixing soups and green chilies together.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa.
Add egg yolks and salt.
Cream until thoroughly blended.
Stir in vanilla and milk.
Cream until of spreading consistency.
Frost cooled cake.

title: crispy chicken supreme
directions: Place Rice Krispies in shallow bowl.
Put in paprika.
Beat egg and add to milk, add flour and seasonings.
Dip chicken in batter.
Coat with crushed cereal.
Place in single layer skin side up in well greased or foil lined shallow pan.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not cover or turn while baking.

title: broccoli-parmesan fettuccine
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water to cover 3 minutes; drain broccoli and plunge into ice water.
Drain and set aside.
Cook fettuccine according to package directions; drain and place in a large bowl.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add Canadian bacon and cook, stirring constantly, 2 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and cook 1 minute or until thoroughly heated.
Add broccoli mixture, whipping cream and remaining ingredients to fettuccine; toss gently.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: apricot nectar
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake 50-60 minutes in bundt pan.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat cookie dough onto ungreased 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until browned; cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine everything, except cheese and chips, in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Combine cheese and chips; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes until lightly browned.

title: paul newman cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on package for a 13 x 9-inch pan. Let cool.
With the end of the handle of a wooden spoon, poke holes in cake, not all the way to the bottom.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over the cake, then pour on ice cream topping. Spread with whipped topping.
Crush candy bars before unwrapping, then unwrap and sprinkle on top of whipped topping.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar, then add eggs and pumpkin. Mix well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in chopped pecans.
Pour into greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: sparkle punch
directions: Combine soft drink powder and sugar; dissolve in milk.
Pour into 6 to 8 soda glasses.
Add scoops of ice cream.
Carefully pour in carbonated water to fill each glass.
Stir slightly. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Combine and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer for about 5 minutes.
Serve hot.
I sometimes use my crock pot for this cider.
To use a crock pot, put all ingredients in the crock pot and turn on high until sugar dissolves.
Then turn heat to low and simmer until time to serve.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef, salt, pepper, onion and green pepper together until onion and pepper are soft.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter play doh
directions: Mix together peanut butter and honey.
Add dry milk.
Knead. If too sticky, add more dry milk.
Store in fridge.
May be eaten.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onions and sugar for approximately 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Chop up and add sour cream, cheese and butter.
(Reserve some cheese for top.)
Put into casserole dish. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: queso dip
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add other ingredients except Velveeta. Stir over medium heat and add all cubed Velveeta.
Heat thoroughly until cheese melts.
Keep hot in crock-pot and serve with tortilla chips.

title: hot salmon dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Heat on low in crock pot. Serve with breadsticks.

title: ham and cheese omelette
directions: In a small bowl, combine the eggs and milk and beat together well.
In a large skillet that is lightly greased, pour in the egg mixture.
As the eggs cook, sprinkle the ham down the center of the omelette and place the cheese over the ham.
(Add onions and green peppers at this time, also.)
Using a spatula, check the bottom of the omelette for doneness.
If bottom side appears to be cooked well, using the spatula, fold in each side of the omelette, overlapping the two sides as they meet and flip the omelette.
Let cook for only a few minutes more.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, sour cream, oil, water and eggs. Beat with electric mixer 2 minutes on low, then 2 minutes on high. Add by hand the chocolate chips and pecans. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Place cabbage in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cabbage.
Cook, covered, for 9 to 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Stir once during cooking period.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: old fashion tomato soup(my mother's recipe)
directions: Cook onion in oil and butter, but do not brown.
Stir in flour (do not brown); add water and tomatoes.
Add pepper and salt and sugar.
Cook slowly until thickened.
When soup is thick, add milk and heat until piping hot (do not boil).
Serve with crackers or cornbread.

title: "ritzy" broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain and add onion.
Add 1/2 stick melted butter and cubed cheese.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top.
Drizzle remaining butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Store in a tightly covered container.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in bowl; dice ham, green pepper and onion very fine.
Mix together and place on cheese plate shaped like a ball.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator for 4 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage.
Drop in boiling water.
Cook 20 minutes and drain.
In buttered casserole, place 1 cup cabbage.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and flour.
Make mixture of salt, sugar and pepper. Sprinkle half of this mixture over cabbage.
Dot with butter.
Add remaining cabbage and seasonings.
Pour milk over all.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Add more butter.
Bake at 375° until bread crumbs are browned.

title: skillet barbecued pork chops
directions: In large resealable plastic bag, combine the honey, barbecue sauce, Italian dressing and chili powder, mix well.
Add the pork chops to the marinade, seal bags, shake to coat meat well then refrigerate for 1 hour.
In a large skillet, cook the pork chops with the sauce mixture over medium high heat for 3 to 4 minutes. per side or until no pink remains.
Serve topped with sauce.

title: gourmet baked spaghetti
directions: Prepare spaghetti as usual.
Mix milk with tomato soup.
In a greased dish, put down a layer of spaghetti; add 1/2-inch grated cheese and cover with some of the soup and milk mixture.
Continue layering to top of dish or to portion desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 45 minutes, depending on amount.

title: raspberry strawberry cake squares
directions: In a bowl, combine oatmeal, cake mix and 6 tablespoons of margarine.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
With remaining crumbs, add egg and mix well.
Press into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling over crust.
To reserved crumbs, add remaining margarine, nuts and brown sugar. Mix thoroughly; sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, salt, eggs and pickles.
Moisten with mayonnaise.
Serve on lettuce or use as sandwich filling.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and margarine. Spread over the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan that was sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: nut lassies
directions: Cream softened butter and cream cheese.
Add to flour and cut in until mixture resembles coarse meal.
With lightly floured hands, form into a smooth ball.
Using a rounded teaspoonful of dough press into tiny cupcake pans so as to make a shell.
Combine egg, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and turn into shells.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then at 250° for 10 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.
Makes about 2 dozen tarts.
I put the nuts into the shells and spoon the egg mixture on top, instead of putting the nuts into the egg mixture.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salty water just until tender. Drain and cool. Alternate layers of carrots, pepper, and onion. Mix together remaining ingredients. Beat well until completely blended. Pour over vegetables and refrigerate over night. This keeps in the refrigerator for up to 2 to 3 weeks.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook until mixture becomes clear.
Add jello and mix well.
Cool.
Place fresh strawberries into a baked 9-inch crust. Pour cooled jello mixture over strawberries.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: no cook apricot-pineapple jam
directions: Pit and grind apricots.
Measure 2 1/2 cups fruit.
Add 1/2 cup pineapple and 1 tablespoon lemon juice to fruit.
Stir in sugar and mix well.
Combine water and Sure-Jell in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir into fruit mixture and continue stirring 3 minutes.
A few sugar crystals will remain.
Quickly ladle into jars.
Cover at once with tight lids.
When set, store in freezer or refrigerator if used within 3 weeks.
This jam is wonderful with freshly baked ham.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or soup kettle brown meat.
Add all remaining ingredients except parsley; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered for 1 hour.
Garnish with parsley.
Yield 3 quarts.
If cooking for 2, soup can be frozen in serving size portions to enjoy months later.

title: no bake chocolate-peanut butter-oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter or margarine and milk in a heavy saucepan; stir well.
Cook over medium heat until the mixture comes to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Take off heat; add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased wax paper.
Cool.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: chicken wings pacifica
directions: Disjoint chicken wings discarding tips.
Arrange in shallow baking pan.
Combine other ingredients and heat until sugar and butter dissolve.
Cool and pour over wings.
Marinate 2 hours, turning occasionally without removing sauce.
Place in 350° oven and bake 45 minutes, turning once and basting now and then.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot or cold.
Makes 20 appetizer servings.

title: pork chops and potato dinner
directions: Place potatoes in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Combine soup and milk.
Mix to blend.
Pour evenly over potatoes.
Set aside. Brown chops in skillet.
Place on top of potatoes. Cover. Bake in a 375° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until tender.

title: black bean soup
directions: Wash and pick over beans.
Put them in a large soup kettle with the water and let soak overnight.
Do not drain.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place rice and water in a Dutch oven. Cook until all water is absorbed.
Add 7 cups milk. Cook this until rice is soft, about 1 hour.
After rice is soft, in a separate pot, bring egg yolks, sugar, 1 cup milk, vanilla and salt to a boil.
Add yolk mixture to rice and stir until mixed.
Pour into a glass Pyrex dish. Beat the egg whites until frothy and put on top of pudding.
Brown in oven about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: picante sauce
directions: Chop all vegetables; add remaining ingredients.
Boil for 2 hours.
Can in hot sterilized jars.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine in heavy bottomed saucepan. Stir over low heat until cheese is soft, margarine is melted and the mixture is thoroughly blended.
Add the powdered sugar and stir until well combined.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in small bowl.
Stir and let stand 1 minute to soften.
Add boiling water and stir until all gelatin is dissolved.
Must be clear.
Stir together sugar and cocoa in small cold mixer bowl.
Add heavy cream and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until stiff peaks form.
Pour in gelatin mixture and beat until well blended.
Heap into a dome shape in bowl and chill 1/2 hour.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over mousse if desired. To double recipe use 1 envelope gelatin and double remaining ingredients.

title: western chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 12 x 8-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
In large saucepan, stir flour into 2 cups milk; blend well.
Stir in mustard, bouillon and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens, stirring frequently.
Add vegetables and chicken; cook 5 to 7 minutes or until vegetables are completely thawed and warm, stirring occasionally.

title: frigidaire fruit salad
directions: Mix cheese thoroughly with two tablespoons of cream.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Cut pineapple into small pieces. Chop pecans.
Seed and quarter Royal Anne cherries.
Chop maraschino cherries.
Combine pineapple, cherries, orange slices, sugar and chopped nuts.
Then fold in whipped cream.
Pour into freezing tray and allow to freeze without stirring.

title: orange biscuits
directions: In saucepan, combine orange juice, 1/2 cup sugar, margarine and orange peel.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 2 minutes. Divide among 12 muffin cups; set aside.

title: splatter
directions: Tape paper in center of newsprint.
Arrange leaves or cut-outs on paper.
Pick up small amount of paint on toothbrush.
Hold screen above paper and rub toothbrush back and forth across the screen to make splatters.
Remove shapes or leaves and dry.

title: cape cod apple pudding
directions: Place apples in a deep pan.
Cook until the apples are tender, adding a little water, if necessary, to keep the apples from burning.
Roll out to fit the pan (baking powder dough made from mix or your favorite recipe of baking powder biscuits).
Spread over the apples.
Cover tightly.
Cook 15 minutes over moderate heat.
Turn out and serve with cream.
Serves 6.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Combine salt, pepper and paprika; sprinkle over chicken. Brown slowly in butter; remove from pan. In same pan, cook onion until tender. Move onions aside and place chicken in pan. Add mushrooms and tarragon and spoon with onions over chicken. Add water; cover and simmer until chicken is tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Saute bread crumbs in oleo.
Combine cream of mushroom soup with hash browns.
Spread in baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover with sauteed bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix 1/2 cup starch with enough cold water to make a paste. Add 2 cups boiling water.
Cool until thick.
Add coloring; cool. Use on dampened butcher's paper.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well all the ingredients.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes longer.

title: scalloped potatoes with pork chops(microwave)
directions: Layer potatoes, onions and butter in 3-quart baking dish.
Mix soup with milk, seasonings and cheese.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover and microwave 20 minutes. Arrange chops over potatoes.
Spoon some sauce over each chop.
Cover and microwave 8 to 10 minutes until meat is tender.

title: cola salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple; heat.
Dissolve gelatins, let cool.

title: fat-free strawberry pie
directions: Mix together the
pudding and jello mixes in one pan.
Pour 1 1/4 cups of cold water in pan and bring to a boil, then remove from heat for 5 minutes.
Arrange slices of strawberries in a pie plate.
Pour jello mix over strawberries and chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, debone and cut into bite size pieces.
Place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups, broth and stuffing mix together.
Pour over chicken. Refrigerate overnight. Set out 15 minutes before baking at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mom b's peanut butter candy
directions: Boil sugar, milk and salt until it forms a soft ball.
Cool slightly, then add peanut butter and vanilla; beat until creamy. Put in 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together.
Use 1/3 cup of mix to 1 mug hot water.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix applesauce, beaten eggs, bananas and sugar.
Add flour and baking soda. Spray bread pan with Pam. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat until smooth (1 to 2 minutes).
Mixture will be thick.
Stir in pumpkin and spices; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate at least 3 hours. Garnish with additional whipped topping and nuts, if desired.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: breakfast sausage strata casserole
directions: Day before serving, prepare strata:
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In large skillet, saute sausage and peppers until sausage is well browned.
Drain.
Stir mustard into sausage mixture. Arrange bread in bottom of baking dish.
Top with sausage mixture, then cheese.

title: dorothy's dump cake
directions: Oil 13 x
9-inch pan.
Dump can of pineapple with juice and spread over
bottom
of pan.
Sprinkle coconut, then brown sugar, then yellow
cake
mix
and
spread evenly.
Cut butter into thin slices
and
dot
over
cake.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Bake in preheated 300°
oven for 1 hour.
Cut into squares and serve with vanilla ice cream.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: pizza burgers(italian sloppy joes)
directions: Brown meat, then mix with tomato sauce and seasoning.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Put into hamburger buns and add the grated cheese or sliced cheese on top.
Close buns and let the heat of the mix melt the cheese.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and freeze.
Thaw partially prior to serving.
Should have the consistency of a slushy.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix in blender.
This dip is good for apples or other fresh fruit.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs real good.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Pour in pie shells and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: no sugar cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is almost gone.
Mix other ingredients; add raisins.
Mix well.
Put in greased pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
When done, cover top with foil for 15 minutes to make it moist.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Drain all the fruit.
Prepare the pudding mix according to package directions.
Fold in the whipped topping and the fruit. Refrigerate.

title: lazy man's cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a casserole dish.
Make batter of flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Add peaches. Sprinkle with sugar.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with ice cream on top.

title: lemon meringue cake
directions: Cream 1/4 cup butter; gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating at medium speed.
Add 2 egg yolks and 1 egg to creamed mixture; mix well.
Combine 1 cup flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9-inch round cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 28 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely.

title: homemade chicken and noodles
directions: Combine egg, salt and milk. Add enough flour to make stiff dough. Roll very thin on floured surface and let stand 20 minutes. Roll up and slice 1/8-inch wide. Spread out and dry 2 hours.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugars, oil and butter. Add egg and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Drop on cookie sheet in small balls.
Dip glass in sugar and press down on each ball.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, soda and salt; set aside in large bowl.
Mix milk, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Beat in egg.
Gradually add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in greased 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in 2 inch squares.

title: aunt peg's cake
directions: Cream together the brown sugar, white sugar, oleo and eggs. Mix in the flour, baking soda, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in the apples and nutmeats.
Pour in a greased pan and bake 45 minutes at 350° until it pulls away from the sides of the pan.

title: zucchini puffs
directions: Combine ingredients, heat oil and when hot drop by slightly heaped tablespoonfuls.
Brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add well beaten egg, vanilla and almond.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Flour hands; shape into balls using rounded teaspoon for each ball.
Then roll in granulated sugar.
Indent top slightly with finger; insert a maraschino cherry.
I use 1/2 cherry for each cookie.
Bake about 12 minutes at 400°.
If available, use butter.

title: mini pecan muffins
directions: Mix together ingredients; set aside. Now beat 6 egg whites until stiff. Mix in ingredients. Put in mini muffin pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool before removing from pan. Makes about 48 mini muffins.

title: chicken wreath
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Saute chicken, bell peppers and onion. Place crescent rolls in a ring on a large round baking stone. with pointed ends facing right overlapping each other.
Add cheese to items being saute and let melt.

Then place meat mixture in center or rolls and wrap end of each roll until the circle is complete. Bake in the oven until the roll are golden brown, about 10 minutes. Use remaining ingredients as a garnish.

title: tandori turkey
directions: Bone the turkey breast and remove skin.
Add all ingredients to a large zipper bag.
Let turkey marinate 8 to 12 hours.
Remove turkey from bag, reserving marinade.
Grill turkey over very hot coals 8 to 10 minutes on each side, brushing with marinade.
Serve with rice pilaf and a fresh steamed vegetable.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frozen fruit
directions: Dissolve 1 1/2 cups sugar in 2 cups hot water.
Add orange juice, 2 1/2 cans water, can of pineapple with juice, cherries with juice, strawberries and bananas.
Mix together and freeze.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Pour into shell and bake.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients (except bread).
Cut top off loaf of round rye bread and hollow out.
Cut top of loaf and residue from loaf into bite sized pieces for dipping.
Pour prepared dip into loaf.
Wrap and refrigerate until needed.
Marbled pumpernickel and rye is also a nice bread to use.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: In a large bowl pour water over Jell-O.
Mix well.
Fold in other ingredients.
Pour half of mixture into 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread half of sour cream over top and then pour other half of mixture.
Put sour cream on top.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: mccarrick's chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In a large frying pan, brown breasts and onion in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add puree and chili powder. Cover and simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Shred chicken into small pieces.
Shred Cheddar cheese into 3 equal piles.
Reserve 2 tablespoons enchilada sauce in separate dish.

title: chili 'n cheese corn dogs
directions: Heat oven to 375°F. Slit wieners to within 1/2 inch of ends; insert 3 strips cheese in each slit.
Unroll dough into 1 long sheet.
Seal crosswise center perforations.
Separate dough into 8 long strips (2 cornbread twists each).
Wrap each strip around wiener, keeping cheese up.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet with cheese side up and ends of dough tucked under wieners.
Bake at 375°F. for 12 to 16 minutes or until golden brown.
Meanwhile in saucepan heat chili according to label directions; keep warm. Serve chili over sandwiches.
8 sandwiches.

title: shortcake
directions: Rub listed ingredients to crumbs.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the mixture for topping to be added before baking.
Add 1/2 cup milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla to remaining mixture.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in a heavy saucepan.
Add butter and milk.
Bring to boil on medium heat.
Stir constantly and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: oriental flank steak
directions: Score steak with knife on both sides.
Pour combined remaining ingredients over steak.
Cover; refrigerate several hours or overnight, turning once.
Place steak on greased rack of broiler pan or greased grill.
Broil or grill, uncovered, over hot coals 15 to 20 minutes, or until desired doneness, turning and brushing with barbecue sauce mixture after 10 minutes.
To serve, carve steak across grain with slanted knife into thin slices.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: miracle fruit cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a saucepan and boil gently for 3 minutes.
Cool in large mixing bowl.
Beat in eggs.
Add fruit cake fruit mix and nuts.
Sift together dry ingredients and add gradually to fruit mixture, beating well after each addition. Pour into a 9-inch tube pan, lined with wax paper.
Can use 4 small loaf pans.
Bake in a very slow oven (275°) for 2 1/2 hours (if using loaf pans, bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes).
Remove cake from oven.
Cool slightly then remove from pan and cool thoroughly.
Wrap securely in aluminum foil or waxed paper.
Store in clean, air-tight container in a cool place.
Age 3 to 4 weeks to improve flavor.
Will store well for 6 weeks.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Allow frozen potatoes to thaw.
Add soup, sour cream, cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° covered for first 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes more.

title: potato cream soup
directions: In saucepan, stir potatoes, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard into cream soup.
Heat gently, stirring frequently.
Do not boil.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: barbecue cake
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with foil.
Dot butter evenly over foil.
Sprinkle evenly with sugar, then with walnuts.
Arrange apricot halves in bottom of pan and sprinkle with lemon juice. Place baked cake on top and cover with foil.

title: super supper
directions: In ungreased 13 x 9-inch dish, blend instant potatoes with sour cream and 1/2 cup water (mixture will be crumbly).
Pat firmly in bottom of baking dish.
Brown ground beef; stir in 1/2 cup water and remaining ingredients except cheese.
Spoon beef mixture over potato mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: mousse au chocolet
directions: Into blender, put chocolate chips and hot coffee.
Cover and blend on high speed until smooth.
Add egg yolks and rum.
Cover and blend on high for 5 seconds.
Beat egg whites in a large bowl until stiff.
Fold chocolate mixture into egg whites.
Spoon into 8 parfait glasses and chill for 1 hour.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Cook in a heavy pan until amber colored.
Do not stir.
Pour over 2 quarts popcorn and peanuts (which is in a large buttered bowl).
Stir until all coated.
Spread on a cookie sheet until cool.
Break apart.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar in large bowl.
Add boiling water and scalded milk.
Let cool.
Add yeast mixture and beaten egg. Stir. Add flour and knead until spongy.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Work down and refrigerate 6 to 7 hours or overnight. Take out of refrigerator. Make into rolls.
Let stand until they rise.
Cook at 400° until as brown as you like.

title: waikiki chicken salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine pineapple, chicken, celery, pimento and almonds in large bowl.
Chill.
Blend mayonnaise, salt, lime rind and juice.
Pour over salad; toss.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream butter and brown sugar at medium speed until fluffy.
Beat in eggs then pumpkin and molasses (it will curdle); set aside.
In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients; gradually mix dry and wet ingredients together until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes.
Knife should come out clean.
Cool.

title: sugarless fruity nut muffins
directions: In pan, combine dates, raisins, prunes and water; bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Stir in margarine and salt; set aside to cool.
Add remaining ingredients to fruit; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into greased mini muffin pans. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 32 muffins.
Can use greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan for 30 minutes.
This is good for diabetics.

title: unbelievable lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.

In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, spread 1/2 of the sauce, top with half of the uncooked lasagna noodles, then 1/3 of the sauce, 1/2 of the ground beef, 1/2 of the Ricotta or cottage cheese, 1/2 the Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese.

title: skier's toast
directions: Simmer corn syrup, butter and brown sugar until it forms a syrup.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice French bread 1 to 1 1/2-inches thick and put on top of syrup, filling bottom of pan. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fried tomato gravy
directions: Slice tomatoes and dip in flour.
Fry in butter.
When thickened, stir in brown sugar and gradually add milk.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Keep warm until ready to serve.

title: light and easy lemon chicken
directions: In skillet, in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown on both sides.
Combine soup and milk, stir in lemon juice and pepper. Pour over chicken; top each chicken piece with a lemon slice.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve with rice and vegetables, yields 4 servings.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine blueberries, cornstarch and sugar substitute in bowl. Mix and coat well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.
Calories per serving 48.

title: one dish casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion and pepper and drain grease.
Put hot meat mixture in bottom of baking dish.
On top, add peas and carrots, chicken soup, cheese and Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with hot rolls.

title: beef barley soup
directions: In large Dutch oven or kettle, heat oil and brown beef.
Add onions, carrots, celery, tomatoes, water and bouillon, bring to a boil, cover and simmer for about 2 hours until beef is tender. Add barley and simmer again until barley is done.
Yields 3 1/2 quarts.

title: london broil marinade
directions: Mix together and marinate.
For London Broil, marinate at least 8 hours.

title: meat rolls milanese
directions: Combine
spinach,
bread
crumbs,
egg and garlic salt. Spread spoonful
of spinach mixture on each tenderized steak; roll as for jelly roll and fasten with wooden picks.
Brown in oil in large skillet over medium heat or flame, then remove.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together oil, eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients in the order listed.
Mix well by hand and bake at 325° in greased tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in shallow baking dish and melt butter in oven.
Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Place caps in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl and mix with fork until smooth.
Mound in mushroom caps.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: nonalcoholic crowd size punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine apple juice, lemonade and orange juice. Stir in ginger ale.
Add ice.
Float sherbet on top.
Add fruit. Serves 58.

title: kraut salad
directions: You may use any vegetable that you would put in a salad.

title: cream cheese dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together with 1/4 to 1/2 cup milk. Add Cool Whip and mix together.
Break cake into small pieces and add to mixture and stir together.
Put in container and let sit in refrigerator for a while.
Top with pie filling and serve.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package instructions.
Mash potatoes; add cheese to potatoes.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients, blending thoroughly.
Chill.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix by hand the cake mix and Cool Whip.
Mix all the ingredients; it will be very sticky.
Use two spoons to drop a teaspoon-sized ball of dough into a bowl (approximately 1 cup) of powdered sugar.
Cover the ball of dough with xxx sugar and drop onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat the 2 eggs together.
Add granulated sugar.
Beat well. Mix first 8 ingredients.
Add milk.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° until firm.

title: crabmeat dip no. 1
directions: Mix in bowl day before.
Spread on 2 x 2-inch party bread. Top with a couple of green olives.

title: grandma's sour cream chocolate cake(from the files of adness williams crutchfield)
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together, then add sour cream and eggs.
Mix well.
Add soda to boiling water and mix.
Beat all together until smooth.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until done.

title: broccoli and cauliflower cheese bake
directions: Steam broccoli and cauliflower.
Place in greased casserole. Beat soup and milk until smooth.
Pour over broccoli and cauliflower.
Sprinkle cheese over vegetables.
Mix Bisquick and oleo until it crumbles and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: hobo cabbage
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
When brown and there is no more redness, chop up and add onion.
When the onion starts to get clear, add the quart of tomatoes.
Let all this simmer in the skillet for about 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Chop the cabbage and add it.
Let this cook until the cabbage is done.
Add salt and pepper.
The cabbage should be done in about 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels fine; melt 1 stick butter.
Mix with 1/3 cup sugar.
Pour over pretzels; mix well.
Bake in 400° oven for 7 minutes.
Reserve.

title: ellen's poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients except Quik and cinnamon.
Pour 2/3 mix in heavily greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with Quik and cinnamon.
Add rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool 15 minutes.
Turn out on plate.

title: turkey party casserole
directions: In baking dish, layer ingredients in order as listed. Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Prepare pie shell (9-inch); mix sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Add pumpkin, eggs, syrup, vanilla and chopped pecans.
Pour into pie shell; sprinkle pecan halves over mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pistachio bundt cake
directions: Mix in bowl on low speed for 1 minute and 3 minutes on high speed.
Pour 2/3 of batter into well oiled Bundt pan.
To the remaining batter, add the chocolate syrup and mix well.
Pour over the batter in pan and run knife through to marble it.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Allow to cool in pan 15 minutes before turning onto plate.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef until crumbly, sprinkle with garlic powder.
Drain fat.
Mix dressing and taco sauce.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl, put just enough dressing to coat.
Serve with remaining dressing.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add Kellogg's Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.
Yields 24 treats.
Has 80 calories and 2 grams of fat.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Grease a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place bread in bottom of dish. Sprinkle grated cheese over bread.
Sprinkle sausage over cheese. Pour eggs and milk over sausage.
Place in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vegetarian black bean chili
directions: Heat oil in medium size saucepan, add onion, red pepper, jalapeno pepper, mushrooms, tomatoes, corn, black pepper, cumin and chili powder.
Cook over medium-high heat 10 minutes.
Add beans, broth and salt.
Cook over medium heat 10 minutes or until boils.
Remove 1 1/2 cups bean mixture to food processor or blender.
Puree.
Return to saucepan.
Add spinach.
Cook until wilted.
Serve.
