Makes 6 servings (11 cups) at $1.26 each with 146 calories per serving, 8 g protein, 2 g fat, 26 g carbohydrates, 373 mg sodium, 0 cholesterol.
To keep fat content low, you may use the nonfat Cheddar cheese.

title: pineapple dressing for fruit salad
directions: Mix all together.
Cook in microwave in a Corning Ware bowl until thick, stirring often.
Cool until cold.
Then add 1 cup Cool Whip or Dream Whip and a package of colored miniature marshmallows.
Mix with drained crushed pineapple, mandarin oranges, cherries, fresh grapes or any fruit of your choice.
Keep refrigerated.
All fruit must be drained.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Line bottom of bowl with lettuce; top with chopped tomatoes, diced ham, chicken or turkey, layer of English peas, top with egg shell noodles, chopped cheese and onion.
Top with Miracle Whip (1 quart jar).
Top with bacon bits.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Toss when ready to serve. I use my punch bowl for salad.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; cool.
Put potatoes, eggs, onions, etc. in bowl.
Put other ingredients in bowl and beat until smooth.
Pour over potatoes and eggs.
Mix.
Chill 4 hours.

title: royal pink salmon patties
directions: Flake salmon, removing bones.
Add all ingredients together and mix well.
Should be very moist.
Make out into patties and brown both sides in frying pan with cooking oil.
Yields approximately 10 patties.

title: unbaked oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a rolling boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and cool a little; add next 3 ingredients.
Mix well and spread in pan.
Cut.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and peanut butter.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add flour, salt and soda.
Form into small balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 9 minutes.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix cracker crumbs and margarine in a bowl.
Spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until brown and bubbly.

title: hot dog dinner
directions: Heat water and bouillon in 4-quart Dutch oven to boiling. Layer potatoes, onions and cabbage.
Sprinkle with salt.
Layer apple and hot dogs on top.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with mustard and horseradish.

title: oven-fried eggplant
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in shallow bowl.
Peel eggplant; cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Spread both sides of eggplant slices with mayonnaise.
Dredge in breadcrumb mixture.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400°, uncovered, for 10 to 12 minutes, or until browned.
Garnish and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: orange coconut cake
directions: Mix these 5 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Allow cake to cool; cut into 4 layers.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Slice and steam carrots for 10 to 15 minutes; do not overcook. Mix soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard and catsup in a boiler. Heat until thickened (10 to 15 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients to carrots.
Pour soup mixture over vegetables.
Chill for several hours before serving.
This recipe keeps for about 1 week if refrigerated in a tightly covered container.
Makes 24 servings with each serving containing 123 calories.

title: cabbage & noodles
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in large, heavy pan. Saute cabbage, onion and mushrooms until cabbage is lightly brown but still slightly crisp, using medium to medium high heat and stirring as needed. Try to keep temperature so that the cabbage will brown, but the moisture will cook off and not make the cabbage soggy. Add sliced kielbasa, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Cook, uncovered until kielbasa is thoroughly heated. While cabbage is cooking add the bouillon cubes to boiling water and cook egg noodles as directed on package. Drain the noodles and toss with remaining butter. Place the noodles on a serving plate and "nest" the cabbage in the center. Great served with hot French bread.

title: estofadong carne(tangy braised beef)
directions: Season beef with salt and pepper.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes. Dredge with flour and brown in hot oil.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of oil in pan; push beef to one side and saute garlic, onion and tomatoes until mixture is mushy.
Add vinegar, bay leaf and enough water to cover beef.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until beef is tender.
Taste for seasoning.
Bring back to boiling; add green beans and carrots and cook until vegetables are done (about 10 minutes).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: black forest dump cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve liquid.
Spread pineapple in lightly greased 13 x 9 pan.
Add pie filling; spread gently. Sprinkle nuts on top of pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over nuts.
Combine butter and juice.
Drizzle over cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool, cut in squares.
Top with whipped cream.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in vinegar, pineapple juice, green pepper, pimento, soy sauce, garlic powder and ginger.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups (20 one tablespoon servings).

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas; cream butter, sugar, eggs, water and vanilla. Add bananas and mix well.
Blend in flour and nuts if desired. Grease and flour baking pan.
Bake at 350° until brown, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: 3-way chocolate buttercream frosting
directions: In a large bowl, blend sugar, butter, vanilla extract and desired amount of Nestle Choco-Bake.
Gradually beat in milk, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until frosting is smooth.
Makes 2 cups frosting.

title: hamburger hash
directions: Mix together until well blended.
Put into 2-quart casserole and cook 40 minutes; remove from oven.
Top with 1 can fried Chinese noodles.
Put in oven and brown noodles.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain; rinse with hot water.
Set aside.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Combine ingredients and store in a tightly covered jar.
For serving, place 1 rounded teaspoon in a cup.
Add boiling water. Stir and enjoy.

title: no name goody
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil, folding over sides. Line saltines all over cookie sheet.
Combine brown sugar with melted butter.
Bring to boil for 3 minutes.
Spoon mixture over crackers.
Put in preheated oven at 400° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over crackers.
Let soften briefly.
Smooth with spoon.
Cover with chopped nuts. Refrigerate 1 hour, then break into pieces.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add beaten egg and molasses. Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: best chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs until well blended.
Add salt.
Stir in flour; blend well.
Add chocolate syrup, vanilla and nuts.
Turn mixture into well greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Smooth top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Loosen edges.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut in squares and garnish with pecans or walnuts halves or dust with powdered sugar.

title: dripless popsicles
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add 2 cups of cold water, Kool-Aid and the sugar.
Freeze in popsicle mold.

title: quick garlic bread
directions: Spread butter on both halves of bun.
Sprinkle with cheese and garlic powder.
Broil until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli (steamed to firmness).
Set aside after cutting in small pieces.
Combine beaten eggs, cheese, soup, mushrooms, salt, pepper, garlic and onions; stir.
Add broccoli.
Mix well in baking dish and bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle 1 can of fried onions on top.
Return to oven and bake another 20 minutes.

title: seafood dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: upstate minestrone soup
directions: Slice sausage crosswise about 1/2-inch thick; brown in oil in deep saucepan or Dutch oven. Add onion, garlic, carrots and basil; cook for 5 minutes. Add zucchini, tomatoes with liquid, bouillon, cabbage, salt and pepper. Bring soup to boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour. Add beans with liquid; cook another 20 minutes. Garnish with parsley. (Soup is even better second day!) Yield: 8 servings.

title: bonnie's chocolate sauce
directions: Melt in a double boiler, then cook over simmering water for 30 minutes.
Great on ice cream.

title: cinnamon swirl pudding cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, oleo, vanilla and water in large bowl.
Blend well.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 10 minutes.
Pour in greased 10-inch tube pan.
Combine cinnamon and sugar throughout batter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Heat soup and cheese until cheese melts.
Add broccoli.
Mix well.
Serve warm with a good cracker.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put ingredients in a casserole dish and stir together.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili pie
directions: Brown ground beef in stock pot; drain well.
Add onion, green pepper, salt, chili powder and sugar.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add flour.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Add stock, tomato puree, tomatoes and corn and cook 30 minutes longer.

title: quick rolls
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add sugar and yeast to warm water. Add yeast water to flour.
Knead like biscuits.
Roll and cut. Place in greased pan.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake in 400° oven until golden brown.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix together the first five ingredients.
Beat egg and milk. Add bread crumbs to liquid and blend.
Pour into meat mixture and blend.
Shape into small meatballs and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: *praline pie
directions: Combine butter and sugar in a saucepan.
Cook and stir until sugar melts and mixture bubbles vigorously.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts.
Spread mixture over bottom of lightly baked (but not browned) pie shell.
Bake in a hot 425° oven for 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Remove from oven.

title: murm's chocolate ice cream
directions: Add the top 5 ingredients to ice cream freezer and fill with cold whole milk.
Freeze.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over moderate heat.
Stir in onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is translucent (about 5 minutes).
Add potato slices and broth; bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to moderate and simmer, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are almost cooked through (about 15 minutes).
Add celery seed and cook 5 minutes longer, stirring frequently to break up potato slices.
Gently whisk with balloon whisk until soup becomes a little smoother, but small pieces of potato should remain.
Season with salt and pepper.
If not serving immediately, you may want to add a little buttermilk or extra chicken broth because soup will get thicker as it stands.
Makes 6 (1-cup) servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon with fork.
Remove skin and bones.
Add salt and pepper; beat eggs.
Add lemon juice, instant onion, cracker crumbs and milk.
Mix well.
Stir into salmon.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Place mixture in pan.
Bake 1 hour at 340°.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla. Add egg and milk. Beat until light and fluffy. Add flour, baking powder and salt. Divide dough in half and wrap in plastic wrap. Chill at least 1 hour. Use half of dough at a time. Turn out on lightly floured surface. Roll and cut in desired shapes. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for
6 to 8 minutes. Cool slightly. Remove from pan. Cool on racks or waxed paper. Frost and decorate as desired. Yields 2 dozen.

title: little pizza on french bread
directions: Mix altogether. Cut French bread in 1/2-inch slices.
Spread with mixture.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.

title: chocolate pie #2
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add Pet milk and water.
Add beaten egg yolks to mixture. Add vanilla, salt and Parkay.
Put this on high heat and stir constantly until thick. Take off and beat lumps out, then pour into a baked pie shell.
Add meringue on top and bake in a 325° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: holiday frozen cranberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and mayonnaise; beat until light and fluffy.
Add cranberry sauce and pineapple. Add nuts, if desired.
Fold in whipped cream and gently blend.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and set aside.
Mix bread crumbs, almonds and seasonings together in a mixing bowl.
Dip chicken pieces in butter, then coat with crumb mixture.

title: monkey cake
directions: You will need a tube pan with solid bottom.

title: pecan shortbreads
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add salt, pecans, flour and vanilla; then mix.
Roll small pieces of dough in palm of hand in shape of a small finger.
Bake cookies in 375° oven for 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: date nut cookies
directions: Chill batter for 1 hour.

title: beans, beans and beans
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Add rest of the ingredients and bake in buttered dish for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Chop all ingredients together.
Use Miracle Whip or mayonnaise, if desired.

title: coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a square 9 x 9-inch pan. Mix flour, sugar, shortening and egg thoroughly.
Stir in milk. Blend dry ingredients; stir in.
Spread batter in pan.
(See Streusel Filling.)
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean.

title: pretzels(bread-like)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt and sugar.
Add melted margarine.
Blend in flour.
Knead dough until smooth.
When kneaded, cut into small pieces and roll pieces into ropes.
Brush with beaten egg; sprinkle with salt.
Bake in oven at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes, until browned.

title: easy fish dinner
directions: Mix lemon juice, sour cream and minced onion.
Spread over fish.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and parsley.
Spread over fish. Pour melted butter over bread crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°. Makes a delicious coating over fish.

title: liver fritada(makes 4 servings)
directions: Fry bacon in a large skillet or Dutch oven until crisp.
Drain on paper toweling; crumble and reserve.
Drain fat from skillet into a cup.
Return 2 tablespoons fat to skillet.
Saute onion in fat until tender, about 2 minutes.
Combine flour and chili powder on piece of wax paper.
Coat liver with flour mixture; add to onion in skillet.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until liver is light brown.
Stir in tomatoes (with liquid), corn (with liquid), salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling; lower heat.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until liver is tender, about 5 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Sprinkle with reserved bacon.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet peppers

title: banana bread
directions: Dissolve soda in sour cream and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs, soda and sour cream and vanilla. Mix well.
Add flour and salt, mixing well.
Stir in bananas. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: never-fail divinity
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water together slowly until syrup spins a long thread when tested with a spoon (246°).
Pour slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites, mixing constantly until mixture thickens and loses its gloss.
Add vanilla and nuts or fruit if desired. Drop by spoon onto waxed paper or prepared buttered cookie sheet.

title: italian vegetable salad
directions: Mix and add Feta cheese.
Let stand 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: apple-cheese bake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar; add cheese, then spice, then add flour.
Mixture will be very stiff and paste-like when well mixed.
Butter a square or oblong baking dish well.
Pour apples in dish and then spoon paste batter over the apples.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 45 minutes.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream the butter with mixture of flour and sugar. Add vanilla and pecans. Shape into form of Brazil nut and bake at 300 degrees until brown. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Place frozen rolls into pan.
Mix dry ingredients in a small bowl.
Sprinkle dry ingredients over rolls. Sprinkle 1 cup nuts over dry mixture.
Pour melted margarine over nuts.
Let rise at room temperature overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon-basil sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan and heat.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add juice.
Add pineapple and cheese, mixing well.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix butter and crackers and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: basque beans
directions: Discard discolored pinto beans; rinse remainder under cold running water.
Drain well.
Transfer to large bowl.
Add enough cold water to cover.
Let soak at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown meat and then place all ingredients into casserole.
Add 2 cups water and mushroom juice.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Top with pecan halves for last 1/2 hour.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Mix well and form into a ball. Chill thoroughly.
Roll out very thin, the thinner the better. Cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes until light brown. Dust with sugar and nutmeg, colored sugar or frost after baking or leave plain.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve all ingredients in hot water; then add cold water. Pour into popsicle molds and freeze.
Keep remaining liquid in refrigerator.

title: ruth's eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant (covered) in boiling water about 10 minutes. Drain. Add remaining ingredients and pour into a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown. Serves 6.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add beaten eggs and beat until fluffy. Add soda in water.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.
Do not overbake.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix sour cream and baking soda.
Set aside.
On top of stove, melt 2 sticks oleo; add 4 tablespoons cocoa and 1 cup water. Bring to a boil; remove immediately.
To melted cocoa mixture, add the sugar, flour, eggs, slightly beaten and salt.
When this is well mixed by hand, add sour cream mixture.
Pour into an 11 x 17 x 1/2 cookie sheet (ungreased).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
DO NOT OVERBAKE.
While cake is baking, on top of stove, melt 1 stick oleo; add 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Beat by hand.
Pour over hot cake as soon as it comes from oven.
One cup chopped nuts may be added to the frosting mix. Makes it delicious.
Cut into brownie size squares when completely cool.

title: mex chicken
directions: Mix chicken pieces, Ro-Tel and soups together.
Mix well.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, layer chips, then chicken mix and top with cheese twice.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until well heated and golden brown on top.

title: mexican dip
directions: Prepare filling:
Blend sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning together.

title: camarones(shrimp dip)
directions: Combine chili sauce, lemon juice, horseradish, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Fold in sour cream.
Add chopped shrimp.
Chill and serve with crop vegetables.
Serves 8.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together and put in serving dish. Cover with cocktail sauce.

title: party ham casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In a large kettle, bring water to boiling. Add noodles and return to boiling.
Boil 3 minutes. Drain and rinse with cold water.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Simmer soup meat in water.
Add salt, pepper, onion and celery.
Cook two hours in large covered pot.
Add corn, tomatoes, frozen vegetables, carrots and okra.
Let simmer for one hour. Add rice and cook thirty minutes.
This recipe should make six quarts of soup.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour 4 cups rhubarb,
cut in 1-inch pieces, in mixture.
Put in pie crust.
Bake at 450°
for 10 minutes, then 350°
for 40 minutes.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Pack in pint jars.
Place 3 peppercorns and 2 large garlic cloves and 1 head fresh dill in each jar.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Pour fruit in bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour dry cake mix evenly on top of fruit.
Cut margarine in thin slices. Put over cake mix, making sure to cover cake mix all over.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: salmon patties
directions: Take bones out of salmon.
Add all the ingredients except save 1/4 cup of the bread crumbs.
Shape into patties and dip both sides into remaining bread crumbs.
Fry in a little oil on both sides until done.

title: jean's hot pineapple cider
directions: Boil water, sugar and cinnamon together.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice.
Boil 1 pint water; add 4 small tea bags and then add to juice.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Top with crushed Ritz crackers that have been mixed with 1/2 cup butter. Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: dump cake
directions: Spoon filling evenly in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread pineapple and juice over filling. Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Slice butter over mixture. Sprinkle with coconut and pecans. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in a greased Bundt pan.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Combine with onion, soup, salsa, enchilada sauce, Cheddar cheese, olives and chiles.
Tear 3 tortillas into pieces 11 x 7 x 2-inch.
Spread half of meat mixture over these tortilla strips.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with Jack cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Can use cream-style corn instead of chicken soup. Serves 8 to 10 persons.

title: terri's creamy onion soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook for 1/2 hour.

title: cherry punch
directions: Mix together.
Just before serving, add ginger ale or Seven Up.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Partially crush chips in bottom of a 9x13 baking dish. Next layer chicken pieces. Mix and heat chicken soup, celery soup, chicken broth, chili powder, RoTels, onions, and green peppers. Pour over chicken and bake at 300° for 20 minutes. Top with cheese slices and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: sonny's cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and pudding until smooth.
Add nuts, marsh mellows and chips by hand.
Bake for one hour in a bundt pan at 350 degrees.

title: no bake turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients for 10 minutes and combine in casserole dish.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove all skin from the chicken.
Rinse and dry the pieces thoroughly.
Season coat each piece with oil or dip in milk.
Shake to remove excess and roll in the corn flake crumbs.
Let stand briefly so coating will hold.
Place chicken in an oiled pan or line with foil for easy cleaning.
Do not crowd pieces.
Bake for 45 minutes or more.
Crumbs will form a crisp skin.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Then mix cheese, eggs, cream of mushroom soup and mayonnaise together.
Then mix all the ingredients with the cooked broccoli at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake the cake and cut into small squares.
Prepare the puddings.
In a large dessert bowl, put half of the chocolate cake at the bottom.
Spread half of the pudding over the layer of cake. Spread half of the Cool Whip over the pudding layer.
Sprinkle the Skor or Heath bar mixture over the Cool Whip layer.
Repeat steps, using the second half of all ingredients.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine the vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and half French fried onions.

title: cheerwine ice cream
directions: Put eggs and milk in double boiler and heat until steaming hot throughout.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat, add sweetened condensed milk and evaporated milk.
Chill. Add cheerwine and put mixture into 4 qt. ice cream freezer container.
Add milk to bring mixture to fill line and freeze.

title: cheese-stuffed shells
directions: Cook jumbo shells as directed.
Drain and dry in a single layer.
In bowl, combine cheeses with beaten eggs, salt, parsley, oregano and pepper.
Fill shell with about 2 tablespoons cheese mixture.
Spread some sauce in a thin layer in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place stuffed shells in single layer.
Pour some sauce on top.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until hot.
Heat remaining sauce and serve with shells.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: southwest chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: molded summer salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, mix in remaining ingredients. Pour into individual mold or large Pyrex dish.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bake pie shell until brown. Mix ingredients in double boiler, stirring constantly. Pour into baked shell. Beat egg whites and make meringue. Pour on top of pie and brown in oven.

title: graham's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain.
Add butter, milk and Ricotta cheese.
In a large casserole dish, layer macaroni, thin Cheddar, macaroni, Monterey Jack, macaroni and thin Mozzarella.
Cook at 350° until brown on top.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar icing. (Dough can be divided and you can add nuts, chocolate chips or coconut.)
If dough is chilled, you can roll into rolls and slice and bake.

title: creamy fruit soup
directions: Drain fruit, reserving syrup (cut up large pieces of fruit). In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine reserved syrup, the 1 cup water, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Remove stick cinnamon. Blend the 1 tablespoon water and cornstarch; stir into saucepan. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice.
Cool to room temperature.
Blend in the sour cream and fruit.
Stir in milk.
Cover and chill.
Garnish with strips of lemon peel, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: working girls' hopping john
directions: Fry bacon in saucepan until crisp.
Add onion and pepper; cook until onion is lightly browned.
Add bay leaf and peas with liquid.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in water and rice. Bring to boil; cover and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar and shortening together.
Add peanut butter; mix well, then add well beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Combine with flour mixture and stir well.

title: okra pickles
directions: Select firm and medium size okra.
Pack whole into sterilized jars.
Add to each quart jar a head of dill and a bud of garlic (or two).
Make brine of water, vinegar and salt; bring to boiling point.
Pour hot brine over okra and seal.
Pickles are ready in 4 to 6 weeks.

title: egg and bacon casserole
directions: Place butter in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Heat butter in a 325° oven for 5 minutes or until melted, tilting to coat dish; remove from oven.
Pour croutons over butter; sprinkle cheese over croutons and set aside.
Combine milk, eggs and mustard; mix well.
Pour egg mixture over cheese and sprinkle with bacon.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes or until set.
Let stand at room temperature 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine Crisco and sugar.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pink pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: tomato beef soup("good for cold winter's lunch")
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Add beef in melted margarine until beef is browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; form into balls and brown in skillet.
Drain.
Heat on stove the brown sugar and ketchup.
Mix well.
Place cooked balls in sauce; let simmer slowly and serve with toothpicks.
May be simmered in a crock-pot on low.
Stir often to avoid burning.

title: brown rice strata
directions: Cook rice with water, 1 teaspoon salt and margarine for 45 to 50 minutes.
Spoon about half the rice into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange broccoli over rice; dot with pimento. Sprinkle with about 3/4 cup cheese.
Spoon on remaining rice in even layer.
Combine last six ingredients and pour over rice mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and almonds.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Uncover and bake at 300° until top is brown, about 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand about 5 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Saute hamburger and onion until done.
Add all cans of vegetables.
Add the juices from all of the cans also.
Heat.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and water chestnuts.
Mix soup and sour cream. Layer beans in casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over beans.
Add water chestnuts.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Top with cracker crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: nishua
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Warm milk; add yeast and let cool.
Add all ingredients except flour and mix.
Add flour, a little at a time, mixing and kneading until all is used.
Let dough rise.
Divide into 3 parts.
Divide each part into 3 parts.
Roll each part in your hands to make a long tube and braid 3 parts together.
Recipe makes 3 braided Nishua.
Put on greased pan and let rise.
Before baking, brush top with 3/4 tablespoon sugar and a little water for glaze.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar after baking.

title: taco salad
directions: Make lettuce and tomato salad in large bowl.
Mix ground beef and beans in salad.
When ready to serve, add grated cheese and crushed Doritos on top.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Use as a dip for
veggies.
(Use fat-free sour cream for a cholesterol free dip.)

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti in small pieces and cook according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Dice onions, cucumbers and green pepper.
Combine with slaw mix.
Prepare dressing.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in ice water.
Add boiling water, sugar, pineapple and lemon juice.
Chill filling in refrigerator.
Break cake in small pieces and set aside.
Line large bowl with wax paper.
When filling is chilled, add 2 packages of Dream Whip. Mix in nuts and cherries.
Place layer of cake and layer of filling alternately in bowl, end with filling.
Return cake to refrigerator.
Chill about 2 hours.

title: nanny's ice cream
directions: Add enough milk to fill the ice cream container.
Use in an ice cream freezer.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Use reserved pineapple juice and water to make 2 cups and bring to boil.
Dissolve jello.
Cool and when starts to gel, add rest of ingredients.

title: jack's secret sauce
directions: Saute onion
in
the
butter
until the onion is clear, then add the pepper.
Stir in all other ingredients and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Best barbecue sauce you've ever had.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook 15 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Grease casserole.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and mix with crumbs. Sprinkle crumbs and paprika on top.
Return to oven for 10 minutes to brown. Serves 8.

title: bible cake
directions: Cream butter and syrup.
Add beaten eggs, milk, honey and raisins or figs.
Add flour into which baking powder has been well mixed.
Add spices of your choice.
Bake as for fruit cake in a 10-inch tube pan, 1 hour at 350°.

title: slow cooker apple butter
directions: Just core apples and cook in the cider until soft.
Run through sieve.
For each 3 cups of pulp, add sugar and spices. Cook in slow cooker on low about 18 hours until thick.
Put in freezer containers and freeze or process in canner for 10 minutes.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 1 cup hot water, add 1 cup cold water. Chill until set.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup hot water, add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Add pineapple.
Fold in whipped cream and mayonnaise.
Pour over lime jello and set.
Dissolve cherry jello in 1 cup hot water, add 1 cup cold water.
Pour over pineapple layer and set.

title: chicken pacada
directions: Debone chicken breasts.
Start with big side and pound to 1/4 inch.
Dip chicken in egg mixture and then in bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in margarine on medium heat.
When thoroughly browned, cover with water in pot and add bouillon cubes and boil for 25 to 30 minutes.
Great over rice.
Sprinkle with fresh lemon.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In a heavy saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla. Cook slightly.

title: kid's sherbet pie
directions: Place softened sherbet in bowl.
Stir in 1/2 tub Cool Whip until well blended.
Spoon into Oreo crust.
Press chopped Oreos down into sherbet.
Cover with all remaining Cool Whip.
Freeze 4 hours.
Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: spanish meat balls
directions: Mix together, make balls, roll in flour and brown in skillet. Put in roaster; cover with chicken broth.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: soda cracker cherry delight
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy; add cream of tartar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold in crackers, sugar and nuts.
Put into ungreased oblong baking dish and bake 20 minutes.
Let cool thoroughly.
Top with Dream Whip (mix according to directions on envelope).
Then top with cherries.
Let chill for 5 hours before serving.
Great dessert to make day before you need it.

title: pralines(from the files of viola clark williams)
directions: Combine baking soda with buttermilk.
Put sugar, buttermilk and margarine in a large pot.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it changes color and forms a lump when dropped in cold water.
Take off heat.
Add 3 cups broken nuts, vanilla and maple syrup.
Fold continually (slowly, about 190 strokes).
Drop on wax paper over a thickness of newspaper.
Makes 80 or so pieces.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend ingredients together well.
Keeps in refrigerator.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating 1 minute after each.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Beat well with electric mixer.
Add vanilla and lemon flavorings.

title: hot jam biscuits
directions: Open biscuits and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cut a cross on the top of each biscuit.
Make an indentation in the center and fill with 1/2 teaspoon jam or preserves.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Top with another 1/2 teaspoon jam.
Serve hot.
Makes 10.

title: individual blueberry pies
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat egg white.
Rinse blueberries in colander.
Roll berries in confectioners sugar.
Empty pie crust mix into a large bowl.
Add butter and egg yolk, cutting into pastry mix.
Sprinkle water and mix until dough holds together; chill.
On lightly floured board, roll out to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut dough into rectangle pieces.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place mound of blueberries on one half and fold crust over berries.
Seal 3 edges with fork.
Seal tart with egg white. Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 15 minutes.

title: macaroni salad for two
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.

title: no fat chocolate cake
directions: Spray 9-inch square baking pan with Mazola.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, baking soda and salt.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Mix the Jell-O and hot water, then add the other ingredients. Congeal.

title: oyster corn bread
directions: Mix corn bread.
If you desire onion, place in corn bread and bake.
Tear up in pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients and put in corn bread.
Mix lightly in order not to bust or tear up oysters. Bake at about 400° in oven for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: norwegian coffee cake
directions: Cut first four ingredients like pie crust until tiny crumbs appear, then take out 3/4 cup and set aside for the topping of the cake.
Now add to the first mixture egg, sour milk and baking soda. Put cake in greased pan and sprinkle "crumbs" on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in large casserole dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fireside shrimp dip
directions: Grate first three ingredients.
Then mix with mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Serve as spread on crackers or as dip with Fritos.
Serves 6.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix in order given.
Cook as pancakes, but don't flip them. If it's too thin, add a bit of flour.

title: potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes, whip and add rest of ingredients.
If using several potatoes, add a little milk.
Place in Pyrex dish; melt butter over top.
Add Parmesan or Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: methodist pie
directions: Put pudding, milk and ice cream in bowl.
Blend together, using a mixer.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze for 1 plus hour.
While freezing the mixture, put the Heath candy bar into food processor and grind into crumbs.
Add Cool Whip on top of base; sprinkle Heath crumbs on top.
Freeze again.
Thaw for 15 minutes before serving.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in processor and puree until very smooth.
Transfer to bowl.
(Can be prepared 6 hours ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)

title: julia's hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup and chips; put in 8 x 8-inch pan.
(Can be refrigerated at this point.)
Pour soup over mixture, do not stir in.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
(Slightly longer if it has been refrigerated.)

title: oriental vegetables
directions: Stir
together
molasses
or brown sugar, soy sauce and vinegar; set aside. Spray a wok or large skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Stir-fry ginger root over medium-high heat for 30 seconds
(wok or skillet should be preheated).
Add onions and stir-fry
for
minute.
Add
pea
pods and cabbage and stir-fry for
more minutes.
Add green or sweet red pepper and
bean sprouts; stir-fry for 1 minute more or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Pour sauce over vegetables and toss to coat.
Heat through.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: grits slices
directions: Pour water over butter and instant grits in 9-inch loaf pan, stirring to blend well.
Cover; chill until firm.
Cut chilled grits in 4 pieces.
Coat each with all-purpose flour.
Beat together the eggs and milk.
Dip each grits piece into egg mixture; roll in cracker meal.
Fry in skillet until golden brown. Serve with syrup.

title: frozen chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and butter and use them to line 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese until smooth, add condensed milk and chocolate syrup.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour mixture into pan.
Freeze 5 hours or overnight.
Garnish with extra whipped cream or grated chocolate.
Store any uneaten cheesecake in freezer.
Serves 8.

title: chops n' rice
directions: Mix all ingredients except the pork chops in a 9 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch baking pan.
Place the pork chops on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 375° until water is absorbed.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix pudding according to box receipt. Layer angel food cake, vanilla pudding, strawberries, Cool Whip and bananas until used all ingredients. Store in fridge.

title: cheese 'n sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients (add a little water if too dry).
Roll into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: seven fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: soup bean pie
directions: Put sugar, margarine, eggs, syrup, vanilla and cooked pinto beans into a blender or mixer.
Mix all ingredients well and then put into pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
The pie will thicken as it cools.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add sugar
and	berries
to
the hot water; chill until thick. Fold in the sour cream and celery.

title: west indies salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Toss again lightly and serve on lettuce.

title: my friend's chocolate pie
directions: Sift cocoa, sugar and flour together.
In heavy pan or double boiler, heat milk.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add beaten egg yolks and cook until thick.
Remove from range; add butter and vanilla.
When cool, pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue made of 3 egg whites, beaten to a stiff froth with 4 tablespoons sugar added.
Beat stiff.
I always use a little cream of tartar for the meringue to stand up good.

title: wild bill's string beans
directions: Add water to just cover beans.
Peel onion.
Cut center of onion out and throw away.
Slice onion about six times and lay on top.
Peel potatoes, slice in uniform slices and lay on top of beans.
Add about 12 drops of Tabasco sauce.
Cook for about 1 1/2 hours on low heat.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in large bowl the ingredients.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased and floured large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Quarter oranges and remove seeds.
Do not peel.
Grind oranges and cranberries.
Add sugar and mix well.
Stir into gelatin.
Pour into 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Yields about 10 servings.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Beat eggs well. Add oil and beat well. Add dry ingredients and beat well.
Add Seven-Up.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: whipped smooth and creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and milk in small bowl.
Beat slowly with rotary beater or at low speed of an electric mixer for about 1 minute.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread on cake at once. Makes about 4 cups or enough for two 9-inch layers.

title: potato soup
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a pot and cover with water. Add a little salt and pepper.
Cook until done.
Pour off most of the water, then put about 1 1/2 cups of milk and 1 can of canned milk.
Heat and add 2 tablespoons butter and thicken with cornstarch in a little milk.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Beat sugars, butter, peanut butter, vanilla and egg vigorously in medium bowl until creamy and well blended. Mix in flour, oats, baking soda and salt. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack. Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: frosted ham salad loaf
directions: Combine meat, eggs, cracker crumbs, pepper and olives.
Shape into round loaf.
Place in a small sack or square of white cloth with ends tied.
Combine hot water and vinegar.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Place loaf on a rack in boiling liquid.
Boil slowly for 2 hours over low or medium heat.
Remove loaf from cloth.
Chill.

title: sticky buns
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, pudding and milk; add to margarine.
Sprinkle cinnamon, nuts and raisins in bottom of pan.
Divide thawed bread dough into 24 balls.
Space evenly in bottom of pan.
Let rise and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour in unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce(per pound of hamburger)
directions: Brown hamburger in the frying pan; pour the grease off and then add the ingredients for the sauce.
When it simmers for a couple of minutes, it is ready to eat.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables as directed on package until almost done. Drain.
Add next 4 ingredients and toss.
For topping, toss margarine with cracker crumbs; sprinkle over vegetables.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coffee cake(don't wait for a coffee break to try this cake.)
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt twice. In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients with milk and well beaten egg.
Add butter and mix well.
Spread into a lightly greased Bundt pan and sprinkle a little cinnamon and sugar on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cover with 2 strips of bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: milk toast
directions: Toast some bread.
Pour milk into a mug.
Tear the toast into strips and dip into milk.
Eat.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all liquid ingredients in a blender or mixer.
Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into greased loaf pan or muffin tins.
Bake loaf for 35 to 45 minutes.
Bake muffins 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool before cutting.
Serve plain or with jam.

title: chuckwagon beans
directions: Cook and drain ground beef, bacon and onion.
Mix together. Then add brown sugar, white sugar, catsup, barbecue sauce, molasses and mustard.
Then add red kidney beans, roka and green lima beans.
Leave some liquid on beans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 11-inch pan.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Mix as listed.
Keep refrigerated.
Will keep for a week or 10 days.
Very good.

title: cinnamon tea cakes
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, at medium speed, beat margarine until light and fluffy.
Then, at low speed, blend in 1/2 cup sugar, flour, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, the salt and vanilla (dough will be stiff).
Chill in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Roll dough with fingers into 1-inch balls.
Place balls 2 inches apart on cookie sheet; bake 10 minutes.
On piece of waxed paper, combine remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Roll hot tea cakes in this mixture. Place on wire racks; cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: rice and beans
directions: Heat up oil.
Add the sofrito, the sazon and the salt and saute it.
Add the beans and add 4 cups of water; let it boil. Add rice.
Lower the flame and wait until water is all dried up. Stir it, cover it and lower flame for 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk and bring to a boil (about 4 minutes). Remove from heat.
Shake in a dash of salt.
Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add cocoa and mix again.
Pour into an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch greased pan.
Refrigerate until hard.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Brown chicken in small amount of oil.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken. Bake covered at 375° approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients, then add the pumpkin.
Sift together the remaining ingredients and add to the first mixture. Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham 'n crescent pie
directions: Place 5 biscuit triangles in "Pamed" 9-inch pie plate.
Press together to form crust.
In a large bowl, combine ingredients and pour into crust.
Roll out remaining dough and cut into 9 x 1/2-inch stripes.
Twist strips and crisscross over filling, tuck under bottom crust and press to seal.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches into baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and egg to crumble stage.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Put margarine over top of mixture.
Sprinkle cinnamon over mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine meal, flour, salt and onions.
Add enough milk to make semi-stiff dough.
Heat oil in frypan.
Use enough oil for deep frying.
Heat to 365°.
Drop dough in hot oil by a teaspoon; turn until golden brown all over.

title: crunchy broccoli casserole
directions: Trim leaves.
Cut off stalks and wash broccoli.
Cook in small amount of water until barely tender.
Combine butter and flour. Blend until smooth.
Combine over low heat, gradually adding milk. Cook until smooth and thick.
Add salt, pepper and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Alternate layers of broccoli, sauce and croutons in 1-quart casserole dish.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Blend cream cheese, butter
and
add other ingredients. Serve with crackers or raw veggies.

title: miami dolphin french toast(can be dietetic)
directions: Put sugar in a large bowl, place cinnamon on top and then add the salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Break the eggs on top and beat the mixture with a fork.
Add the milk and continue to beat and then add the vanilla and mix it all together real well.

title: onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter until soft.
Add sugar, flour, salt and pepper; blend well.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add stock gradually, stirring well.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add wine.
Pour over toasted French bread.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: low-fat chicken marsala
directions: Pound chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thickness.
Dip in Egg Beaters and then coat with cracker meal.
Set aside.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat. Add milk and coconut. Beat eggs, then add milk and chocolate.
Add sugar.
Stir until blended good.
Bake in pie shell in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: northern style lasagna
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook bacon until crisp; spoon off fat.
Add beef and onion; cook thoroughly. Spoon off fat; add spaghetti sauce.
Set aside.

title: tempting apple crisp
directions: Place apple slices in a shallow baking dish; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry ingredients; add melted butter, mixing until crumbly.
Spread mixture over apples.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serves 6.

title: pasties (welsh)
directions: Mix together flour, salt
and
shortening;
add milk by teaspoon.
Mix together until mixture forms a ball.
Roll into balls
to
make 4 to 6 individual pies.
Place each pie square onto
cookie
sheet.
Put
in
layers
turnips
or	rutabagas, sausage
patties, onion, hamburger patties and sliced carrots. Add dot
of butter and pepper.
Wrap dough around each, pinch corners and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.
Yields 4 to 6 small pies or 2 regular pies.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix and pour into freezer.
Fill to line with cold milk (less than 1 gallon).
Follow directions to freezer for freezing.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread slices, crusts removed and place in greased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Brown and drain sausage (drain off fat).
Spoon sausage over bread. Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: blackberry preserves cake
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: grandma's lemon cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs with fork until well blended. Stir in oil, vanilla and lemon rind.
Blend in sugar until mixture thickens.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add to egg mixture.
Dough will be soft.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Stamp cookie flat with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Lightly oil glass, then dip in sugar.
Continue dipping in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need a clean plastic flowerpot.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix pineapple, onion, celery, pecans and raisins together in large bowl.
Mix pepper, salt, garlic, chicken base and mayo together and stir into chopped ingredients.
Mix well and fold in diced chicken.

title: angel hair pasta with chicken
directions: Make Ahead.
Prepare chicken as recipe directs.
Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator up to 2 days ahead.
Simply reheat and serve over pasta.

title: sweet potato casserole(grated)
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla together.
Add grated potatoes (raw).
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 13-inch baking dishes. Bake at 350° for about 2 hours or until done.
Stir the pudding about every 30 minutes during cooking to be sure all the potato pieces are evenly cooked.
(You may season pudding with 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 teaspoon nutmeg added before baking.)

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° in greased and floured Bundt cake pan for 55 minutes or until done.
Makes a large, good cake.

title: burger mushroom bake
directions: Combine 1/4 cup golden mushroom soup with ground beef, bread crumbs, egg and onion.
Mix thoroughly and shape into 6 oblong patties.
Place in shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Combine remaining soups and water.
(May need to add more water to soup to make sauce appropriate consistency.)
Sprinkle with dried parsley flakes and paprika.

title: meatball sandwiches
directions: Place precooked meatballs in a large saucepan.
Add pasta sauce; cook on low for about 20 minutes.
Slice deli buns in half; fill with meatballs.
Top with lettuce, tomato and cheese.

title: chicken halves piquant
directions: Place chicken halves, skin side down, in shallow foil-lined pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and brush over chicken.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 45 to 50 minutes, turning after first 25 minutes and brush occasionally with sauce.

title: adirondack blueberry pie
directions: Take 1 cup of berries, add 3/4 cup water and boil 5 minutes. Add sugar mixed with cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Add the remaining 3 cups of berries.
Pour into baked pie crust. Cover with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: hot potato casserole
directions: Shred cooked potatoes.
Add sliced scallions.
In separate mixing bowl mix soup, sour cream, and milk; mix well with wire whisk.
Stir into potatoes and onions.
Fold in Cheddar cheese; add salt and pepper to taste.
Heat in 350° oven for 40 minutes

title: chicken casserole
directions: Rub chicken with butter, salt and pepper and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove skin and bones when cool and cut chicken in small pieces.

title: peek-a-boo squares
directions: Grease small cookie sheet.
Spread half of batter out of pan. Next, spread fruit filling over batter.
Spread remaining batter over filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple fruit dip
directions: Combine dry ingredients in saucepan; blend in fruit juices. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is clear, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Slowly stir into the beaten eggs.
Return to saucepan and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, 3 to 5 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Beat cooled mixture into softened cream cheese.
Chill overnight.

title: shrimp stuffed peppers
directions: In cooking pot, size to hold 2 quarts of water, put salt, garlic and peppers.
Bring to a boil and boil 10 minutes.
In separate pot, boil 1/2 cup raw rice, drain.
Mix soup, lemon juice, pepper, onion and butter.
Heat, then add rice, parsley and shrimp.
Stuff peppers with shrimp mixture and top with 1 cup grated Swiss cheese, 6 pats of butter and paprika (for color). Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in 4 quarts boiling salted water until tender. Stir occasionally while cooking.
Drain and rinse with hot water. Separate noodles and hang over edge of colander.

title: leona's fruit dip
directions: Stir together ingredients, adding juice to make it the consistency you like.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat sugar and cream cheese until well mixed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Turn mixture into crust and top with pie filling. Refrigerate 2 or 3 hours.
It's ready!

title: puppy chow
directions: Spread nuts in shallow pan.
Roast in oven at 300° for 15 minutes.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Return to oven until butter melts.
Stir to mix thoroughly.
Roast additional 10 minutes.
Remove and salt to taste with garlic salt plus regular salt.

title: cream cornets
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Gradually add sugar, beating constantly, until stiff but not dry. Beat in flour and almonds.
Spoon heaping teaspoonfuls of batter onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Spread batter to make mounds 2-inches in diameter. Prepare only 6 at a time.
Bake in very hot oven at 450° for 3 to 4 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool a few seconds and carefully remove from cookie sheet with spatula.
If cookies stick, return to oven for a few minutes. Roll with fingers, overlapping cookie to form cones.
Press overlapped ends at wide end to seal and hold shape.
Cool and just before serving, fill with sweetened cream.
Makes 2 or 3 dozen.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Toast pecans approximately 15 minutes at 375°.
Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Chill until ready to freeze.
Add pecans just before freezing.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: In bowl beat cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread mixture on serving plate.
Top with nuts.
Serve with apple wedges.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters, 1 can at a time. Shake in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place in greased Bundt pan.
Cook oleo and brown sugar until dissolved, then boil for a minute or two.
Pour some of this over each can of biscuits in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Turn out on plate.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour mixture on peaches that are cut in half. Bake at 300° for one hour.
Lightly brown.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine and mix thoroughly:
flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add egg, shortening and hot water; add orange juice to make total of 3/4 cup liquid.
Add cranberries and nuts. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: one egg cake
directions: Note:
You can use any other kind of fruit if you wish.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix together by hand and shape like a ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: scorpion
directions: Combine ice, rum, brandy, sweet-sour mix and orange juice in a blender container and blend. Serve in a 14-ounce old-fashioned glass. Serves 1.

title: old southern sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook on low heat until thick.

title: "more"
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Fry meat and onion until brown. Mix all ingredients and place in a baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese and bake in moderate oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together with a wooden spoon.
Add beer and mix well.
Turn into a greased bread pan.
Melt butter and drizzle over top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes one large loaf.
Excellent toasted.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, brown sugar and vanilla in large bowl.
Add flour, baking powder and salt and sift.
Mix 3/4 package of M&M's to dry ingredients; mix well.
Add to creamed mixture. Use rest of M&M's to decorate tops of cookies. Drop by rounded spoonfuls.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes.

title: sorghum taffy
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in a 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cook until mixture spins a thread (soft crack stage).
Add soda, stirring to blend thoroughly.
Turn out onto buttered platters.
Cool until candy can be handled.
Butter hands and pull taffy until light colored and too stiff to continue pulling.
Pull into long twisted ropes.
Cut or break into pieces; wrap in wax paper or plastic wrap.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, onion or chives, and pimento (if desired); mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles, pressing perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture into center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners up to center top and pinch to seal.
Brush top with remaining melted butter and roll in croutons.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: venison soup(serves 3 to 4)
directions: Cook meat in water for 1 hour.
Add onion, potatoes and half of seasonings.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes, corn and remaining seasonings.
Cook 30 more minutes.

title: breakfast hot puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin cups.
Mix shortening, 1/2 cups sugar and egg thoroughly.
Stir in flour, baking powder, allspice and milk alternately.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full and bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: the ultimate chicken soup
directions: In a 6-quart pot, simmer chicken, celery, carrot, onion, peppercorns, cloves and salt in 4 quarts of water until chicken falls apart.
When cooked, remove chicken from pot; let cool, then skin, bone and tear into pieces.
Set aside.
Strain broth and return to pot.
Add chicken bouillon cubes, stirring to mix well. Stir in cream of chicken soup; stir to dissolve lumps.
Bring to a boil.
Add noodles and cook 6 minutes.
Stir in chicken pieces. Add parsley flakes, red pepper flakes, minced onion, black pepper and additional salt, if desired.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Melt butter in shallow baking dish.
Dip chicken pieces in flour.
Place skin-side down in butter. Sprinkle with paprika, lemon-pepper and garlic salt.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken pieces.
Sprinkle again with seasonings. Bake 20 additional minutes.

title: sandwich - hot bologna
directions: Cut hot dog buns in halves.
Grind together bologna and cheese.
Add salad dressing.
Spread butter and filling on buns. Wrap with foil.
Heat in slow oven at 300° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: no toss salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order in 9 x 13-inch serving dish. Sprinkle with garlic salt and cover with mayonnaise.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap and chill 4 to 6 hours.
Before serving, add more bacon to the top.
Also add 2 grated hard-boiled eggs.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Pour milk (& water or regular milk) into saucepan, heat to almost boiling.
Mix sugar, flour, egg yolks vanilla salt -add to hot milk, stirring till mixture thickens.
Add coconut. Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
For meringue, beat egg whites until peaks form.
Add 3 Tbsp sugar and 1 tsp vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes. Spread on custard in pie shell.
Sprinkle with more coconut.
Brown in 350 degree oven.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, covered, in salted boiling water to cover for 35 to 40 minutes, or until fork-tender.
Peel warm potatoes; slice.
Add onion.
In large skillet, cook bacon; remove from heat.
Lift out with slotted spoon; set aside.
Pour off fat. Return 1/4 cup fat to skillet.
Stir flour into fat in skillet. Add sugar, butter, salt, pepper, vinegar and 1 cup water.
Bring to boil, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream.
Add potatoes, onion and half of bacon; toss gently.
Sprinkle with rest of bacon and chopped parsley.
Serve warm.
Makes 10 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line bottom of pan with 2 bananas.
Mix pudding and cup of milk, then vanilla, sour cream and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix Cool Whip in last.
Pour half, then put in bananas and fill with the rest.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into cake pan (9 x 9-inch). Make 3 indentions into mixture.
Pour vanilla in one, oil into another and vinegar into the third one.
Pour 1 cup cold, cold water over this and mix well.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Do not attempt to remove from pan; serve from pan.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: white lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed and drain.
In a saucepan melt margarine; blend in flour, onion, garlic powder and pepper.
Add chicken broth and milk; cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in the first 1/2 cup grated cheese and mushrooms.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 of noodles, all of asparagus, chicken and Mozzarella and 1/3 of milk mixture.
Top with ham, remaining noodles and remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and pepper on a piece of waxed paper. Coat tomato slices with flour mixture.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add tomatoes in a single layer. Cook 3 to 4 minutes per side until lightly browned and just barely tender.
Remove to serving platter.
Repeat with remaining butter and tomatoes.

title: banana torte
directions: Crust:
Mix (food processor works great) and pat the flour, margarine and walnuts into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden and then cool.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken with salt and pepper, remove from bone.
Place chicken in casserole.
Add soup and chicken broth.
Place flour, milk and margarine on top of chicken mixture.
Place hard-boiled eggs on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
This is real good as a main dish.
Good.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small cubes; this will take about 2 months. Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire for about 4 weeks at 465°.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If this isn't enough, add 2 rabbits only when necessary, as most people don't like "hare" in their stew.

title: peanut butter surprise sundae(mrs. z. original)
directions: Heat peanut butter and marshmallow whip together on high for 30 seconds in microwave.
Whip together with fork.
Scoop ice cream into bowls.
Top with peanut butter mixture.
Drizzle chocolate sauce over top.
Whip cream and cherry on top.
Great after a light dinner or leftovers.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips over low heat and cool slightly.
Add nuts and marshmallows; mix.

title: white frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together and put in large loaf pan.
Sprinkle with coconut and freeze.
Will keep up to 6 weeks.
(Don't have to use coconut.) Can add other fruit.
I like adding a fresh peach and cut in chunks.

title: lasagna with broccoli and mushrooms
directions: Oil 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cook the lasagna noodles until just tender; drain.
Heat the oil over medium heat, add mushrooms and broccoli and cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: fried squash and onions
directions: Wash and cut ends off squash.
Slice.
Peel onion and slice thin.
Set aside.
Place margarine in heavy skillet over low heat and melt.
Cover bottom of skillet with half of squash.
Sprinkle half of salt, pepper and flour over squash.
Spread half of onion over squash.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Cover skillet with tight fitting lid.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Turn with spatula and cook about 10 minutes longer to brown other side.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pie crust(makes 2 crusts)
directions: Boil water and oil; pour over flour.
Stir together.
Divide; roll on floured board.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Take drained juice from cherries and pineapple.
Bring to boil. Stir in jello until dissolved.
Add 2 cups Coca-Cola.
Let chill and add remainder.

title: herb rolls
directions: Put margarine, parsley, dill seed and cheese into a 9-inch metal pie pan.
Melt over low heat.
Cut each biscuit in half and swish each piece in the butter.
Arrange pieces so they all touch. Bake from 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: whipping cream biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix ingredients together.
Roll out on floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into biscuits.
Bake until lightly browned.
Reliable!

title: impossible pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, Bisquick, eggs, margarine and vanilla in blender.
Cover; blend on low for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand about 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all of the ingredients	and
roll
into a ball; then chill for several hours.
Can
be
rolled in chopped nuts before chilling.

title: rolls or loaf bread
directions: Canned milk, diluted with water, may be used.

title: potatoes and ribs for a crowd
directions: Spread a layer of kraut in roaster, then a layer of sliced onions.
Follow with sugar, spread over kraut and onions.
Spread the meat next with tomato paste on top.
Quarter potatoes and add to pan when meat is about half done.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream soft butter or margarine with peanut butter and sugar. Drop on cookie sheet by rounded teaspoons.
Flatten in crisscross pattern with a fork and bake for 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven. Let cool, then place on plate.
(Chocolate chips can be added.) Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate custard
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: bran apple coffee cake
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter.
Combine 1 cup cereal with 1 cup boiling water; set aside. Cream the granulated sugar and 1/3 cup butter.
Beat in eggs. Mix in milk, applesauce and softened bran.
Combine the remaining flour, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add the remaining cereal and egg mixture; blend well.
Pour into two greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Sprinkle half of the cinnamon mixture atop each. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: You also need 1 large punch bowl.

title: breakfast cornflakes or lunch cornflakes
directions: Fill bowl with cornflakes.
Pour milk over cornflakes and eat. No sugar, please.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Makes 44 cookies.
Happy eating!

title: sloppy joes
directions: In skillet, cook beef until browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Add soup, water, Worcestershire and pepper. Heat through, stirring often.
Serve on buns.

title: lemon-orange pound cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cake is done when center springs back when touched lightly with finger.
Let cake cool for about 5 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat (hamburger, Italian sausage or mixture).
Discard grease.
Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in olive oil until translucent.
Add tomato puree, stewed tomatoes, Parmesan cheese, spices and meat.
Simmer covered for at least 1 hour, preferably 2 hours.
Add water to desired consistency.
Serve over spaghetti noodles and enjoy!

title: brenda's spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix sauce and seasonings to taste.
Brown hamburger and Italian sausage and drain.
Add tomato paste.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine the graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick butter.
Put into pan.
Beat the powdered sugar, 2 sticks butter, eggs and vanilla. Pour over graham crust.
Add the sliced bananas and pineapple. Spread evenly.
Top with the Cool Whip and place candied cherries on top.

title: garden spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and salt to taste.
Serve with crackers or as a sandwich spread.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease dish.
Wash, pare, thinly slice potatoes and onions.
Cover in small amount of boiling water with 2 teaspoons salt for about 5 minutes or until slightly tender. Drain.

title: teriyaki cornish hens
directions: Combine melted butter and seasoned bread crumbs.
Mix well. Place hens, breast side up, in a shallow roasting pan.
Stuff with croutons mixture.
Combine soy sauce and garlic.
Brush on hens. Bake at 350° about 1 hour, basting every 15 minutes with pan drippings.
During last 15 minutes, garnish with mandarin oranges and return to oven.

title: holiday red rice
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil; simmer for 10 minutes, covered.
Just before serving, add apples and oleo.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together sweet potatoes, sugar, 1/2 cup margarine, eggs, vanilla and condensed milk.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: italian pork noodles
directions: Cut pork into cubes and stir-fry with 1/2 teaspoon oil, chopped onion and mushrooms.
Stir in diced tomatoes and Italian seasoning.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Put everything in blender except sour cream.
Mix until smooth.
Add sour cream and chives.
Blend.
Serve cold with dill garnish.
Serves 6.

title: vanilla sugar cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar and margarine in large bowl.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking soda, and cream of tartar. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Roll half of dough at a time, 1/8 in. thick on surface dusted with powdered sugar.
Cut into desired shapes.
Placed onto ungreased or parchment lined cookie sheet.
Bake 7-8 minutes or until light brown.
Remove cookie sheet.
Makes about 5 doz. 2 in cookies.

title: crickets(cookies)
directions: Beat butter, sugar and light brown sugar on high until light, 2 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add vanilla in with the last egg.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix on low just to combine.
Fold chocolate covered raisins and pecans into mixture.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 12 minutes, just until golden. Recipe yields 4 dozen.

title: aunt nez's pound cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and eggs alternately.
Add salt and flavorings.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: chinese chews
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and dry ingredients. Add vanilla and nuts last.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweeter muffins
directions: Mix oil, milk and beaten egg together; set aside.
Combine flour and sugar together and mix in with egg mixture.
Stir in your favorite berries and fill a greased muffin pan 3/4 full of batter. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 small muffins.

title: chocolate sunday pie
directions: Combine cookies and melted butter and spread in an 11 x 14-inch pan.
Spread vanilla ice cream over cookie layer.
Heat chocolate and butter; remove from heat and add sugar, salt and milk; cook until thick (10 minutes).
Add vanilla and almond flavoring.
Cool and pour over ice cream.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle some cookie crumbs on top and freeze.
Take out 10 minutes before serving. Make the chocolate sauce first.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients except marshmallows.
Put in a greased baking dish and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Raise oven temperature to 450°.
Cover top of pudding with marshmallows and continue baking until marshmallows are golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: squash relish
directions: Wash and put through food processor squash and onion.
Add salt and stir.
Let soak overnight.
Drain.
Mix together red vinegar, sugar, dry mustard, cornstarch, pimento, bell peppers, turmeric and black pepper.
Add squash mixture to vinegar mixture and cook about 45 minutes on medium heat.
Put in jars and seal.
Yields 8 pints.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix pudding with milk until thick. Add Cool Whip and stir until smooth. In a 13 x 9 inch dish, put a layer of graham crackers, then pudding mix. Add another layer of graham crackers and pudding mix. Make 3 layers. Spread cherry pie filling on top and chill until ready to serve.

title: toasted coconut-pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly combine eggs, sugar, butter or margarine, lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven 45 to 50 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool.
Garnish with sweetened whipped cream and pecan halves if desired.
Serves 6.

title: "in a jiffy" jiffy squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8-inch brownie pan. Mix by hand all 3 ingredients together.
Pour mixture into prepared pan and bake for 30 minutes.
Let cool completely and cut into squares.
Yields 9 squares.

title: christmas wreath
directions: Use double boiler.
Melt oleo; then melt marshmallows.
Add green food coloring.
Stir until everything is melted and blended. Add cornflakes.
Stir until everything is coated green.

title: no bake cocoa cookies
directions: Melt sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in a pan.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Boil for 2 minutes. Stir in oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Plop on waxed paper and cool to harden.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix and freeze in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: corn and crab bisque
directions: Saute onion and margarine together. Then add remaining ingredients.
Cook together and add more milk if mixture is too thick.

title: "grace's" strawberry preserves
directions: Place
sliced
strawberries
in
colander; pour boiling water over
berries.
Drain.
Place
berries
in a heavy pan. Add
2 cups of the sugar; bring to a boil.
Boil slowly for 5 minutes, then
add
2 more cups of sugar.
Boil for another 5 minutes.
Let set overnight.
Seal cold;
refrigerate.
Keeps several
months in refrigerator.
Great on hot cakes, waffles or any hot bread.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add potatoes, salt and beaten eggs and water.
Add 1/2 of flour. Beat until foamy.
Mix in rest of flour.
Mix until stiff.
Let rise until light or double its bulk.
Then mix down and keep cool. This will keep for several days.
Knead a pan as needed.
Make into rolls and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken
and
pick
off
bones.
In bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan, put
layer of chicken, a layer of grated cheese, a layer of crushed
Doritos,
layer of sliced onions and can of diced Ro-Tel. Pour
can	of mushroom soup, can of celery soup and 1/2 can
of water
over
the layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(You can also
put
a
